animal.description:
Please Share! 
Everyone meet Winnie! This sweet girl is a Weimaraner, about 1-2 years old and 50#-ish. She came to us from Southern WV a few weeks ago, but had a bit of an upper respiratory infection so she could not be cleared for foster at that time.. Winnie did well in boarding in Jefferson County NY, and she is now doing great, but needs to find a foster or foster to adopt to help show her the ropes. Winnie is very friendly, very active and seems to get along with most dogs very well. She does seem to have a high prey drive for smaller animals, however, and on leash will try to chase birds, squirrels and smaller animals so we are looking for a home for her with no cats or pocket pets. She needs help with basic obedience and would do best in a home familiar with Weimaraners or other hunting breeds so that she can get the training and exercise that she needs. This poor girl was dumped in a common dumping ground for dogs at a mine in WV, let's show her that not all humans are bad and her life IS worth saving!

Please copy and paste a completed adoption application from our homepage with your inquiry if you would like a response back. We get dozens of emails and phone calls each day with only an hour of "free time" to volunteer and answer them around our full-time jobs and family life...don't let your inquiry get passed by because of an incomplete application. Thanks in advance for your help!

Help our rescue by donating to our "Spay the momma fund". When adopting one of our babies, if each new family would contribute an extra $10 we can help out that babies mother by assisting with the cost of her spay. Help turn the momma into a pet rather than a breeding factory, donate today! 

Adoptions limited to a 500 mile radius of Pulaski, NY and pets must be viewed in person by all family members prior to adoption; animals will not be shipped to their new homes. Veterinary reference check and adoption donation also required. Check out our homepage for a full list of our adoption requirements.

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

animal.description:
Please go to petresqinc.org to fill out an adoption application in order to meet Raya:

Meet Raya. She's a 3 year-old. 21 lb. Australian Sheep Dog/ Corgi mix, or an Aussie-Corgi or Augi. She's totally housebroken, a mix of cuddly mush & explosive energy. She likes to run, chase thrown toys, or get as close to you as she can & nap. She expresses herself by lots of kisses. She also barks in excitement when she meets new friends, or if she's startled by sirens & other loud noises. When lights go out and it's time for bed, she sleeps through the night a good 8 hours. Raya is current on her vaccines and is microchipped. Raya will need a proper/slow introduction to other pets. She does startle easily and is unsure of new things. She is going to need patience to help her be her best self.

animal.description: Dossie is a 13 week old female retriever (best guess) mix. This adorable little girl came in absolutely terrified and it is clear that someone was not very nice to her. She has slowly started to warm up but she is going to need a dedicated family to continue to work with her and show her that not all people are bad. Due to Dossie's shyness, she cannot go to a home with children and would do best in a quiet environment. We are looking for a family with previous dog experience and we think that she would thrive with a canine companion. ***PLEASE NOTE*** If you are interested in adopting, please submit an adoption application on our website. We receive hundreds of applications for each available puppy and we are looking for the best match for each dog. Please allow 1-2 weeks processing time after submitting your adoption application and notify your landlord, vet and/or references that we will be contacting them.

"Heyya! My name is Sweetheart, and I just joined the adoptable doggy crew at Providence Animal Center. I'm originally from Florida, around 1 year old (2 in a couple months), about 42 pounds, and I'm all set to move right into your heart & home today - already spayed, microchipped & up to date on vaccinations. 

They didn't pull my name out of thin air - the staff have learned that I'm a super sweet gal. I'm also a pro at taking treats gently (cheese is my favorite!), and I've mastered sit, down, paw and high five. I love my outside time, taking walks with and hanging out with my humans.

As much as I love my PAC people, I'm really looking forward to finding my forever family. The staff think that I'll thrive with a family who has owned dogs previously and where the kids are 15 & older.

The staff would love to match you with your new best friend forever - and hopefully that's me! If you are interested in meeting me in person, please schedule an appointment here: ProvidenceAC.org/AdoptADog. Can't wait to meet you very soon! XOXO Sweetheart"

-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!
-------

Providence Animal Center relies on adoption fees and donations to save pets! Adoption fees vary per pet. To find out this pet’s adoption fee or for more information, please call the Adoption Center with this pet’s ID number.

Can’t adopt? Consider fostering or donating! Visit https://providenceac.org/support-us/ for more information on how you can support the lifesaving mission!

animal.description:
Go to Perfectlyposhpaws.org and fill out an adoption application if you would like to meet sweet Lucy.

Hello there,

My name is Lula and I’m looking for my new family. Even though the pictures show me as looking a bit more serious, I’m far from it.

I’m a super sweet, gentle, loving girl with a calm demeanor. I get along with everyone I meet from dogs, cats and kids. I absolutely love being with kids, it’s so much fun.

I’m good natured, even tempered and just a complete love bug. I don’t bark and I am friendly with everyone. I enjoy walking up yo people and saying hi.

I don’t bark, not demanding in any way and would make the vest companion dog.

If your looking for a buddy to keep you company on cold nights, watch TV and hang out on the couch then I’m your gal.

I enjoy belly rubs, ear scratches and sitting by your side. Take me hone and I promise to be the best dog ever.

Cant wait to meet my new mommy and daddy. I ill give you butterfly kisses.

Love and Licks,

Your girl Lucy

Missy is a tiny pocket pointer who came to us last month from a small shelter near Corpus Christi. She may be small, but she makes up for that with her happy, spunky personality. 

She loves people, is supper sweet, and is great with dogs once she warms up to them. She will need slow intros at first, and a little time to decompress, but then warms up and loves to play. She is crate trained, and enjoys exploring. She does have a high prey drive, so we don’t recommend a home with cats. 

Want to adopt this sweet girl?  Visit canerossorescue.org to apply. She is currently being fostered in the Houston area, so this might be a great chance for anyone there to meet her more easily.

Directions: I-44 to Exit 161, turn south towards Fort Leonard Wood, travel 1.9 miles to the third stoplight from the interstate and turn left to enter our parking lot.

CATS
All cats and kittens adopted from Kitten Division Adoption Center are spayed/neutered, have received age appropriate core vaccinations, tested for FeLV, microchipped, flea and tick preventative, and dewormer. Our standard adoption donation is only $95 for one or $165 for two of our fully vetted adoptable cats and kittens, though some breeds may be higher. All cats and kittens are required to leave in a carrier. Please bring a carrier or you can purchase a cardboard carrier from us for $5.
https://www.facebook.com/KittenDivision

DOGS
NOTE: Dogs and puppies reside in foster homes where arrangements can be made to visit them. They are NOT housed at Kitten Division Adoption Center. For more information about a puppy or dog, call or text 573-567-0076

Dogs and puppies adopted from Kitten Division Adoption Center (aka Puppy Division) are spayed/neutered, have received age appropriate core vaccinations, tested for heartworms (if over 6 months old), microchipped, flea and tick preventative, heartworm preventative, and dewormer. Adoption donation varies based on age and breed of the dog. All dogs and puppies are required to leave with a collar and leash. Please bring a collar and leash or you can purchase a collar/leash set from us for $15.

animal.description:
Oh my goodness, hiiiiii!! My name is Nikki, and I am sooo excited to meet you! I just arrived to Stray Haven on 12/21, and I have had a crazy life so far. I have been bouncing around from place to place. I was living with my past owner in his truck for awhile before I came here. It was kind of cramped and I didn't have much room to play. But now I have a whole yard to play in, and I hope you do too! I also went to stay at this other home for a little while... I wasn't getting the exercise I needed and I started herding the small kids there! It's not my fault I promise! I just sometimes get a little rough when I'm playing. I love to run and bounce around. I LOVE to talk and make sure you know I'm around. I love to eat as well! I will eat whenever, wherever and whatever you let me have. I'm super affectionate and I take no time to love up on you if you're sweet. All I really want is a stable home with loving owners... That's the life. If you're up for it come on down to Stray Haven.
Stray Haven Humane Society & SPCA
194 Shepard Rd., Waverly, NY 14892
(607) 565-2859, www.strayhavenspca.org 
Open hours (winter): Tues, Wed & Thurs Noon - 6pm; Sat 10am-4pm

usually with 48 to 72 hours. The whole process can take a week or longer depending on how many applications we receive. Please understand we are volunteers, we work, have families and holidays on top of volunteering to save dogs on days off, evenings and weekends. 
 

 Hi Chester here! I'm hoping to move up north soon as I think I'm going to love the snow with all my hair! A little about me! I'm a young boy and have a lot of energy! That's the husky in me! With all my energy I might accidentally bowl little children over so maybe some siblings that are a little older. If you don't have any children that's ok too as I'd devote all my love to you! I can't go to a home with kitties because I like to chase them! I'd love to come home with you!!

$600.00 Adoptioni fee. He will be coming from Houston, Texas to Vermont. His adoption fee INCLUDES his neuter, shots, health certificate, Martingale Collar, and transport fee.

animal.description:
Oh, Little Peggy Sue! 

Video: https://youtu.be/gdfiBWZOXOY

1.5 years and about 45 lbs, shes a little thing! She is Outgoing, active, and excited. She Wants to be with her people. She is not a champ yet in the crate but she is working on it. She would LOVE a home with someone who can be with her a lot of take her to work with them. She is fine with getting a bath. She Looks for your approval and wants to please you. She did well with the dogs we introduced her to, see video. She was Good passing other dogs at pet store.

She was great with the kids we introduced her to and she gave them kisses. She gets excited and a little jumpy but calms down. She Does fine in the car. 

The doctor says she looks great and seems to be in great health. 

She listens with instruction just needs some direction and basic training. We need someone who wants to do basic training to set her up for success. She will need some kind of daily exercise.

 

No cats please. 

 

Peggy Sue will make someone an awesome companion!

 

Questions to alayna@ThreeLittlePittiesrescue.org

App here: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/30283/generic

The adoption fee is $550. He/she is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 2-6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee!

she is arriving in the PNW 2/8/21.

Please inquire by submitting an application to Alayna@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/19753/generic

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families.

MEET HARRY POTTER:

Harry Potter is a 1 year old, 50lb Lab mix (possibly mixed with Golden Retriever). He is sweet, social and friendly! He is good with other dogs that have equal upbeat energy! He is currently in a high intake shelter and in order for us to save him he will need a foster home! Not much is known about his interaction with small breed dogs, cats, very young children or his understanding of house manners, however all of that will be an integral part of his assessment before being placed in foster home that meets his needs. Furever Tails Animal Rescue is responsible for the cost of heartworm treatment and follows the American Heartworm Society protocol. Dogs treated for heartworm lead normal healthy, long lives!

Furever Tails Animal Rescue covers all the costs for the care of the animals in foster homes. We provide food, supplies and the medical costs required to ensure we are adopting out healthy and happy pets! Fosters are not required to continue fostering for any specified amount of time, and if foster parents fall in love with their foster pet then they have the first option to adopt! 

Furever Tails Animal Rescue is based out of northeast Oakland County. Our vet offices are located in Clinton Twp, Lake Orion, Oxford and Romeo. It would be ideal if the foster home was within range of our approved vet offices in case of medical emergencies or basic preventative care.

Fostering is such a rewarding experience! Many of the lives we save are those in great risk of being euthanized for no fault of their own. Saving a life can be as easy as opening your home for a temporary period of time while we process applications for a lifelong furever home!

animal.description:
This animal is presently available at the Richland Hills Animal Shelter. Hours of operation are Tuesday thru Friday, 11 am - 6 pm and Saturday 11 am - 4 pm.

Adoption fees for dogs are $80.00 (unless otherwise noted), which includes vaccinations, spay/neuter, and worming. Adoption fees for cats are $65.00, which includes vaccinations and spay/neuter. CALL FOR DISCOUNTS AND SPECIALS. 817-616-3769

Adoption fee waived for veterans, active military, city employees or seniors in Richland Hills. (*except for puppies or kittens)

 We are always looking for volunteers and donations. If your church/school or any group wants to hold an adoption fair or fundraising event please give us a call for available dates.

animal.description:
I came into foster care after being saved from a shelter where they were going to euthanize me and my babies. A wonderful foster mom and her family took us in and are very loving to us. I however just have a hard time trusting people and keep my distance as I am trying to figure out the role of a human, how they can help me, but most importantly, don't want them to hurt me. With time, love, consistency and patience though, I will come out of my shell soon!

If you are interested in adopting, please visit our website and complete an adoption application at www.elpasocountycanine.org/available-dogs

animal.description:
Hi my name is Fletcher! I am 7 months old and a Lab/Collie Mix. My foster mom says I am super sweet and I love everyone. Sandi Paws rescued me with a fractured fibula and tibia in the rear left leg. I also had a tibia tarsal luxation, and had an extreme fixator in my left leg. I also had a wire and screws in my right leg. I had to go to the vet because I had a reaction to the hardware that was in my right leg and I had to have it removed. I am being fostered with six kids of all different ages. I get along with cats and dogs of all different ages and sizes. I am potty trained, crate trained, and leash trained as well. If interested please go to SandiPawsRescue.org for more information you can also find volunteering information as well.
Thank you for your interest in a Sandi Paws Rescue, Inc. Please visit our site at sandipaws.org for more information on our organization or to fill out an application to adopt one of our pets. You can find information for volunteering o. our site as well.

animal.description:
Age (best guess based on teeth): Born 11/28/2020

Size (full grown best guess for puppies): Mom is 30lbs unknown dad

Information: These babies were surrendered from an owner who is now getting mom spayed. Since he is older he did not want to deal with a litter of pups. These babies have had limited socialization with others. There are a couple that are very shy, but otherwise loving and playful. These babies are furry for a Texas heeler so we think dad was a poodle or collie mix. 

 

We are a foster based rescue based out of Muskegon, MI. We have an application process for adopting our pets. We have an application on our website www.caninesrescue.com. PLEASE DO NOT EMAIL US WITH YOUR APPLICATION INFORMATION. WE REQUIRE YOU FILL OUT THE FORM. We check vet references, backgrounds for abuse or neglect and home ownership or speak to the landlord to verify you are allowed to have a pet. Once the application is received and approved then we will set up a time for you to come and meet our pups that are available. All our dogs are up to date on shots, microchipped, been dewormed at least once, and sterilized. All meet and greets are APPOINTMENT ONLY. We do not have a facility that the public can come and view our pets at.

animal.description:
*Due to state laws regarding out of state adoptions, we cannot adopt to families in Massachusetts or Rhode Island.*

Dover is a sweet 10 week old pup ready for his forever home.

Listed breed is an educated guess made by our veterinarian and is NOT a guarantee - this also means we have no way of knowing what a puppy's adult size will be.

This dog is currently being fostered in Mississippi and will be transported via Barton's Barkers transport services upon adoption. Their adoption fee is $500 and includes spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, a nose to tail vet check, microchip and transport costs. Second Chances lists dogs as being available in White River Junction, VT because we transport our dogs to the area every 3rd week after they have been adopted. All of our local shelters have a high euthanasia rate due to overpopulation so we created our rescue group to primarily adopt to the northern states to help keep as many dogs as we can from entering our kill shelters.

I used to call the shelter in Grand Forks my for-now home, but my luck wasn't great over there, so I thought I'd try to find my permanent home here at GRR! I'm a youthful and interesting pup who loves a quality snack, and believe me, I'll let you know if the snack is quality enough for me. I enjoy being around my people, but can be quite independent and aloof at times. If you're looking for a young, but distinguished lad to join your pack, then look no further! Please contact GRR about adopting me today!Visit http://www.greatriverrescue.com/adoption-2/ to learn more about our adoption services.

animal.description:
If you love decadent, delicious, and delightful desserts, then MatchDog has your dish! Welcome the Cutie Pie Pups - chock full of fluffy morsels to tempt your sweet tooth! Indulge today!

Are you ready for a special sweet treat to be your everyday delight? Meet our sweetest boy, Pandoro! Named after a super-sweet Italian cake, Pandoro is a 10 POUND 4-month-old male Boxer blend with a curious and playful nature. He is great with other pups and kids, too! Pandoro is doing well with his house manners and is ready to learn all the tricks you can teach him! Boxers are known to be intelligent and upbeat, with wonderful silly personalities. Are you ready to make this little treat your daily dose of sweetness? Apply for Pandoro today!

If you think you are a perfect match for Pandoro please complete an application fully: https://www.petstablished.com/organization/243592 

Pandoro has been fully vetted, is up to date on all vaccinations and on preventatives for heartworm, flea, and tick. We cannot guarantee breed information. You will find price guidelines for adoption at matchdogrescue.org and you can read about the whole adoption process and what MatchDog Rescue provides with each dog.

This gorgeous MatchDog is currently being fostered and cared for at our own facility so as to look and feel his best when he meets you on Saturday, February 13, 2021. For the very best chance of securing a meet with this dog, you must be available all day on this date. 

If you see a pending notification on this dog, it means we have informed the lucky family selected as the best match for this particular dog and they have agreed to come to the transport/event with the goal of taking the dog to their forever home. If for any reason this plan falls through, we will change the picture back to its original format and revisit other applications.

animal.description:
Groundhog Litter
Meet Punxsutawney Phil
DOB: 9/26/20
Male Mother: Lab/Staffie Mix, Father is presumed to be a Hound mix based on characteristics
Weight: 30lbs

ADOPTION FEE: $250.00
AVAILABLE Wednesday 2/3
APPLY TO MEET HERE: https://form.jotform.com/202887123155152

This litter of Labs, Phil, Thistle and Chuckles, are super sweet and want nothing more than you! Need some Love this Valentines' Day well any of these puppers will take all care of that! Their owner could not take care of them and asked for our help. Of course we are fixing the Mama so they won't have this happen again! 

Phil is named for Punxsutawney Phil the most famous groundhog and considered the official weather predictor. According to the lore, there is only one Phil, and all other groundhogs are impostors. It is claimed that this one groundhog has lived to make weather prognostications since 1886, sustained by drinks of ""groundhog punch"" or ""elixir of life"" administered at the annual Groundhog Picnic in the fall

ADOPTION FEE: $250.00

All our adoptable dogs are spayed or neutered, micro-chipped, dewormed, UTD on age appropriate DA2PP & Bordetella Vaccines as well as on Heartworm & Flea Preventatives.

*READ ALL - COVID 19*

WE ARE OPEN BY APPOINTMENT ONLY & MASKS ARE REQUIRED. 

Our facility is currently CLOSED TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC. 

YOU MUST APPLY AND BE APPROVED TO ADOPT TO GET AN APPOINTMENT

APPLY TO MEET HERE: https://form.jotform.com/202887123155152

Applying does not commit you but rather gives you permission to meet & adopt if you choose to.

ONCE APPROVED WE WILL CALL & EMAIL YOU - APPROVALS CAN TAKE A FEW DAYS

** WEEKEND APPLICANTS **
WE ARE CLOSED SUNDAY & MONDAY THUS YOU WILL NOT HEAR BEFORE TUESDAY

We realize that you are excited & anxious to know but calling us daily to check keeps us from working on the applications & delays the process. 

ONLY ONE APPLICATION NEEDED 
If interested in more than one pup just put all the names on one application. If you already have an approved application then just email us at lchsmanager@gmail.com to tell us you which animals you want your approved application applied to.

Only approved applicants wearing a MASK will be allowed to enter our facility and meet our pets. 

Please do not request an appointment if you or anyone in your household have had symptoms of COVID 19 or been around anyone that you know has been positive or experienced symptoms within past 14 days. It is of the utmost importance that our staff stays healthy so our pets can be taken care of. After someone leaves our facility everything is cleaned with bleach water for the safety of all!

All our pets are posted online and we continue to take applications until they are actually adopted. Many times things change and an approved adopter does not adopt the animal so we do maintain a wait list when necessary. 

Thank you for reading this and following the directions. It is a part of our approval process!

APPLY HERE: https://form.jotform.com/202887123155152

ADOPTION FEE: $250.00

animal.description:
Meet sweet Hank. Hank is a 10 month old American Staffordshire Terrier/mixed breed. He'd a medium sized dog, about 45-ish pounds. He is a social guy with people and other dogs. He came to us from Apache Junction where he was an owner turn in. He is a loving guy and puts himself to bed every night at 8 pm! This handsome guy is residing at our adoption center and can't wait to find a forever family to love.

We currently do not require appointments but this is subject to change due to the current COVID situation (masks are required). We will be monitoring the number of people in our building when we are open, so please be patient if you are asked to wait outside until we help families that arrived before you. If we feel our dogs would not do well with other dogs or with young children, we will state it in their bio - if it doesn't mention it, then we will do introductions with your dog(s). If you're interested in this dog, please go to our website at www.azfriends.org and fill out a consultation form, then just come and see us!All animals are altered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, licensed (dogs). Cats tested for FELV/FIV. Dogs tested for Heartworm. All animals are available to the first family that is a good match, and if we have more than one animal who is a good match, there will be a lottery for all matches. Note that families must have come in to our adoption center and spoken with an adoption counselor prior to any lottery (when we have lotteries, they usually occur on Saturday mornings).

animal.description:
Amora is a two year old Kelpie mix (according to county but she looks more shepherd mix to me ) weighing in at 35 lbs. She's the momma to the Love Pups and has spent the last 8 weeks in her momma role but the time has come for Amora to find an amazing forever home of her own 

Amora came to us very under socialized and has warmed up in our home very well. She is such a lover and enjoys being with us whether that means laying at my feet while I work or snoozing with us while we watch TV. Her forever family should be prepared to continue to work on her socialization and should understand that there will be a warm up period for her in her new home. Meeting new people can sometimes be a little overwhelming for Amora so introductions with no pressure allowing her to make friends at her own pace work well. 

Amora does well on car rides, sleeps well in her crate and walks ok on her leash (this is an area that could benefit from some more work). She tends to get startled when cars drive by but we feel that this is something that would go away with more exposure and practice. She is also potty trained and uses the dog door. 

Amora would be great as an only dog or a companion to a dog of her size or larger who is on the mellower side and not necessarily looking for a play/wrestle buddy. Amora has done ok co-existing with our dogs but has not really saught out play with them. She has however recently learned that toys are fun to play with on occasion and enjoys tennis balls and carrying stuffed toys around in her mouth. 

One thing we have noticed about Amora is that her prey drive instinct is present. For this reason it is important that Amora's forever home not have any cats or other small animals (chickens, birds, bunnies, etc).

Amora is a special girl and has won our hearts. She has her quirks (like chasing the wind and biting at rain drops ) but she's hard not to fall for. We know that the perfect family to help Amora continue to blossom into the great dog we know she can be is out there and we're beyond excited for her and what her future life holds.

Amora will be available for adoption on our website on Wednesday 2/3 at 7pm.

Peaches was adopted as a kitten and as family circumstances changed now returned to rescue 6 years later. Shes beautiful and has many years of love to give the right family. This beautiful girl will need a few weeks to adjust but will make an amazing new member to your family!

Please note, we receive a large number of applications. We appreciate your patience as we complete our review processes. A personal interview, reference checks, meet and greet with pet, home visit and a solid vet history are required for adoption.

Apply for consideration to adopt at www.ruffdogrescue.org

animal.description:
Little Wesley is about as sweet as they come, and he is crossing his paws that hell soon find a home to call his own! Wesley is one of mama Arias boys (along with Fenrir, Tom, & Wheeler). Aria is an itty-bitty pittie mix (around 40lbs), but we arent sure who Wesleys daddy is...so we cant guarantee what his size/weight will end up being. Wesley is currently 5 months old and weighs about 25lbs. He is a smart little boy, and has been picking up quickly on his potty-training routine. He alerts his foster family that he needs to go out by ringing the bell on their door. He can be a little bit nervous with new human friends, but hes still young and impressionable and tends to warm up pretty quickly! Wesley loves other dogs and would definitely benefit from having another confident dog in the home, but this isnt necessarily a requirement. It is currently unknown how he would do with cats, but since he is still pretty young we think he would adapt and be ok. In general, Wesley is a quiet boy who loves to hang out for naps in his kennel. He has been sleeping through the night, and he is a good little eater. He also does well with the [older] kids in his foster home. If there are kids in Wesleys forever home, we would recommend they be ages 8+, as currently Wesleys least favorite thing is when his foster humans pick him up. Therefore, any kids in his home should be old enough to understand how to positively work with him on this and/or to not pick him up. He is such an adorably sweet boy, and we cant wait to see him settle into his perfect forever! 

If you are interested in adoption Wesley, please submit a general adoption application at https://newleashdogrescue.com (or private message us if youre already preapproved!). 

**Wesleys $250 adoption fee includes his neuter, vaccines to date, and microchip.

animal.description: Meet Rosey! Rosey is a 2 year old female with similarities to a Chiweenie. animal.description:
This blue-eyed, handsome hunk recently found himself euth listed in an overcrowded Texas shelter. With the help of a partnering organization, Muddy Paws was able to bring Oso and 12 other young dogs 900 miles to rescue. Oso is now safe, warm, and adjusting to his new beginning. He's still acclimating to his new environment (and climate!) but his foster says that Oso is a big, gentle, sweetheart who likes to lounge on the couch or relax in a comfy bed with his favorite people. Oso is definitely one of our new fosters who is diggin' winter weather; he is loving being outside right now and, as a big boy, he'll need a large, fenced yard to explore and play. He gets along with other dogs and has his leash manners down pat! We'll continue to post updates about Oso's personality and furever "wish list" as we learn more. Welcome to rescue, Oso!

The suggested adoption donation for Oso is $400 We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes. 

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver. 

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months. 

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
If you have ANY QUESTIONS or are truly interested in adopting any animal from PAW Animal Shelter Please, fillout an adoption application FIRST! WE are a high intake No Kill Shelter ran by a staff of 4 and do not always have time to answer every question asked by so many. If you are a good fit for the animal you are interested in -we will call to speak with you, If we feel you are not a good fit , we will contact you about other pets that may be a good fit for your home. Many people are losing the opportunity to adopt the animal they want because they fail to put in an application and the pet was adopted before we could answer your email. .If you have applied for an animal in our facility and have not received a response within 7 days, PLEASE call or contact us again. Though we do our best in trying to answer all emails in a timely manner, sometimes things get away from us, get lost or misplaced. It is never our intention to ignore a request about an adoptable animal in our facility.

Sandy Brown, Director, PAW Animal Shelter

Name: Duke (Male)
Breed: Pit Bull Mix
Adoptable in: MA, RI, NH, CT, and VT

Good with dogs: Yes
Good with cats: Yes, dog savvy cats
Good with kids: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it
House trained: Mostly

Duke is a gentle giant who is very loving and active. He loves playing with toys, especially tennis balls, long walks, car rides and snuggles with his humans.

Duke gets along well with other dogs and enjoys playing. He would chase cats given the chance, but takes correction from them. He never meets a stranger and loves all kids, little and big. He is not a fan of the crate, but he is quiet inside it, although does his best to work his way out of it. He is house trained with a doggy door, but he may need to adjust to a home without one. He loves a leash because it means he is going for a walk!

Please Note: All dogs currently available for adoption are posted on our website. If you cannot find a particular dog on our website, he/she may be on a temporary foster hold. All dogs are otherwise posted until they are officially adopted. This dog may have other interested adopters in line. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application.

animal.description: Cookie, cookie cookie - do you love cookies? Then come meet Cookie Monster! This active, mischievous, playful, smart, loving, and goofy boy loves affection, cuddles, and other canine playmates. It's hard to resist his hyena face and adorable white paw. He is also a super cuddler, and loves to be near his humans when they are chilling out. He will lay his head right in your lap and gaze soulfully into your eyes. He also loves to be in the middle of his humans on the couch. Cookie takes a bit to warm up to new humans and men are especially scary to him, so patience and time is something that he will need. Cookie could potentially be an excellent exercise dog, and he would love a home where he can be active and get some nice long walks during the day. He is a smart pup who can sometimes be a bit stubborn, and he needs continued training on manners - he can pay and nip at his humans when he wants attention. He also has an adorable quirk where he steals socks - forget losing your socks in the dryer, Cookie will take them all! He has another adorable habit of making lots of little grunting and barking noises when he zooms! Cookie needs to be in a crate when his humans are away on their pesky errands. He will typically whine while his humans are away. His foster family has been crate-training him, and he's doing better. He enjoys eating treats and sleeping in his crate, but prefers not to be left alone in his crate. He has also made huge strides in his potty training, and has been going to the door when it's that time of day. Cookie has been learning his leash training and would love a family to continue with his leash manners because he can be reactive to other dogs and other people on the leash. He is generally very well behaved, but needs some additional training when it comes to human food. He has been working really hard, and is doing much better. An ideal home for Cookie would be one that is adults only, with parents that are around a lot and who have training experience. He would do best in a low traffic home with a yard, and lots of activity and structure. If you are looking for that adorable Cookie Monster to cuddle with, then come meet this sweet boy and let him steal your cookies!

animal.description: Yam Is such an adventurous boy. He's already explored and socialized in Austin's Zilker Park and the dog park, warming up to new people he meets. He's eager to play fetch with people at the park. Then at his new foster home, this playful, energetic boy is excited to play fetch with balls and sticks of every size and play tug-o-war with his rope toys. And if his humans will pet and brush him, he's even happier. This very loyal, friendly youngster (also known as Cooper) is also a very kind boy. His foster is disabled and mostly in a wheelchair, so Yam is very gentle and obedient with him, fetching balls and leaving them on his lap. And he goes on slow walks with him. He's also protective of his doggie housemate, playing and then napping together. And he's getting along well with a visiting retriever and kids, wanting to play with them, too. Yam is a smart, quick learner who knows 'come,' 'stop,' 'sit,' 'lay,' 'wait,' 'no bark,' and 'come get a treat.' He's made good progress on his leash-walking skills. And he's a house-trained boy who sleeps well in his crate. Unleashed, he'll go to the yard to potty, run up and down and explore some curiosities, then return within minutes. He's a very lovable boy who will be a best friend his family can count on for love and loyalty. Come meet him, he'll be so happy to be your caretaker!

animal.description: This puppy came from a family over in Illinois that couldn't keep him., we really don't know what breed to give him for this listing.  He's 3 1/2 months and weighs maybe 12 pounds. .  Our adoption fee includes his neutering which was done, a vet exam with a fecal check, puppies first , second and third series of his DA2PPV, his bordetella vaccination, his first  series of his Canine Combo Influenza H3N2 and H3N8 , deworming , a package of free doggie day camp , grooming and a dog training consultation once a month for 4 months. You'll also receive anytime in the first year of your adoption at the same place a full day of doggie day camp, one free night boarding  , a bath or grooming and a coupon for dog training , a bag of dental dog bones, a doggie toothbrush, 2 free bags of puppy food, 2 months of flea and tick preventatives', one month of a heartworm preventative, a great coupon booklet you can use at any that has many money saving coupons off your puppy supplies at any Petsmart store plus the booklet offers a free hotel stay at any of the Petsmart that have a hotel, a 30 minute dog training consultation , a free day of doggie day camp and there is a coupon for Banfield to have a free vet exam .  The rescue group had the vet put a microchip in the puppy at the time if neuter.  The microchip company offers the adopter a free 30 day health insurance offer that you can activate if you want health insurance for your puppy . An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
URGENT!!! URGENT!!! URGENT!!! URGENT!!!
THIS POOR OLD GUY NEEDS A SOFT PLACE TO LAND! WILL YOU BE HIS HERO???
Bernard or Bernie as we call him is looking for either a new foster or furever home! He is a approximately 8 years old, mixed breed, approximately 60lbs, neutered, microchipped,  and up to date on vaccines. He is a sweet boy who only wants to spend time with his people.  Would do best as an only dog. Bernie was pulled back in July from the local shelter and has been in a foster home this whole time but the resident dogs have decided that they don't like Bernie very much anymore so we need to move him asap. 

If you are interested in fostering or adopting Bernie please copy and paste the link below to your browser and complete our application at https://daniellethedogrescuer.wufoo.com/forms/zq5l29b022pyq0/

FROM HIS PREVIOUS FOSTER MOM:
                                                                      
Bernie has been my foster since about July 2020. He was introduced to my 3 dogs and did great. I had a 5' field fence surrounding almost a 1/2 acre where he loved to run, explore and play.  He was great until I moved in November. Around October my alpha dog Duncan passed away then in November I moved to a new location. Unfortunately The new place did not have a secure fence for a couple of months and Bernie had to be let out on a runner. He was not happy as he loves to explore. By the time I got the fence up and let him loose with my other 2 dogs there was conflict and animosity between them. Hindsight now suggests that it was probably a combination of them jockeying for the newly open alpha position, the move, and the stimulation of the new neighbor dogs running the fence line. . Before this they were all fine together.    Bernie has never shown any aggression towards people. I can take away food, bones, toys, whatever and he's fine. He does have a prey drive for small animals like bunnies, birds and squirrels. Not sure about cats but wouldn't chance it. He is an absolutely sweet boy and loves people and spending time with them. If walked on a leash he is best suited to a no-pull harness but then again I never really had time to work with him since he had major surgery on his ACL a month after coming to me and took 3 months to heal. Currently, he was injured in an altercation by my other dog and will need some time to decompress and settle into a new home without any additional dogs bothering him until he fully heals. I was told that he was 8years old but it was probably due to his deteriorated condition. Based on his energy level I seriously doubt he's older that 5 years old.  Bernie can be an opportunistic runner. We were teaching him the "back" command when opening the front door and he was doing much better. One time after he ran the neighborhood exploring he ended up at a neighbors back yard and when I got there he  was interacting with their little child of about 5 years old.  Bernie was good with him and the child was hugging him around the neck. Bernie was very accepting of the interaction. He has never dug to get out of the yard. He just looks for opportunities like a broken/low part of the fence or a place where he can squeeze under if the fence is loose.   I did find that Bernie doesn't like to be crated.  He generally barks and gets very upset but does calm down after a while but sometimes the stress upsets his stomach. The only time I ever had to crate him is when I went out of town and had a professional sitter watch him. Although resistant he was able to be coaxed to go in the crate. He wasn't a fan but was able to be lead into it fine. Usually I never had to contain him since he was always a great boy in the house.  While he LOVES to chew his toys he never chewed or destroyed anything in the house. Bernie is very smart and trainable. When he first came he wasn't house broken but learned to potty outside within a week and never had an accident after.

animal.description:
Good, good Leroy Brown...the goodest boy in the whole dang town!  That's me!  I am Leroy Brown and I am a 4 month old, 30lb., pit bull terrier mix little man.  I still have some growing to do but I think I will be about medium to large size when I am full grown.  I am already hard at work learning all about house training and crate training.  I will need someone to help me really get those down and teach me all kinds of other fun stuff!  I do know how to "sit" when asked politely!  I am a smart guy so we could really learn some cool stuff together!  I need a home with a 6ft privacy fenced yard (no apartments for me).  I am good with other dogs my size or bigger and would adore having one in my forever home!  I am also good with older kids.  I have a paw with some nerve damage that will heal over time.  It doesn't slow my handsome brindle butt down!  I am such a fun, playful, affectionate love muffin!  I need an active home where my humans are home more than not.  Ready for your life to get really good?  Well, fill out my adoption application and you'll have the goodest, bestest, most handsomest fella to love you forever and ever!  

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
This sweet Terrier mix is named Hollar. He's 4 to 5 months old and he weighs between 20 and 25 pounds, his mature weight probably between 35 and 40 pounds. Hollar came to us from the kill shelter, and we're so glad. He's handsome in his medium length coat of mostly black, his perky ears, and his deep chocolate eyes. Hollar gets along very well with other dogs, kids and his foster's cats, too! With that temperament and those good looks, he'd be a great family dog. (posted 1/30/21, TN)
**It is rare that we know with certainty the ages or mixes that make up our dogs, but we do our best to be as accurate as possible based upon our experience. **
Adoption: $350 which covers quarantine, shots, worming, food, medical records, spaying/neutering,microchip and an Alabama State Health Certificate.
Transport, if needed : $140.00 We consider the transport to be of great importance and, as such, take particular care of the dogs during the trip from Alabama. We make every effort to arrive with healthy and minimally stressed dogs.

animal.description:
https://apath4paws.org/adoption-application/ (copy and paste into your browser)

YOU MUST FILL OUT AN ADOPTION INTEREST AT THE ABOVE LINK TO BE CONSIDERED FOR AN APPOINTMENT.

WE WILL BE SCHEDULING APPOINTMENTS FOR THE PUPPIES BASED ON THE APPLICATIONS RECEIVED. THE PUPPIES WILL NOT BE AT THE ADOPTION CENTER ON THE WEEKEND. IN ORDER TO OBTAIN AN APPOINTMENT YOU MUST FILL OUT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION INTEREST.

Olympus is about  4 months old and currently weighing about 20  lbs. The pups were found in the middle of the desert with no housing around the area.   They were brought in as strays and no owner came forward.  It was suspect that they were driven out there and dumped.   More will be known about me soon.  

This breed is very loyal to their family and does not generally allow rehoming into another family if their first family does not/can not keep them for life.   PLEASE consider, this is a LIFETIME commitment for this breed.  Originally bred to guard livestock, shar-peis are alert, intelligent and protective dogs who make excellent guardians. They possess a calm and devoted nature that makes them loving companions. They tend to be aloof with strangers, but are fiercely loyal and affectionate with their own people and love to spend time in the company of their families. 

By providing them with socialization and obedience training as puppies can also make them easier to handle as adults, as shar-peis are strong-willed dogs whose personalities may overwhelm an unprepared pet parent. These dogs do best with confident, assertive leadership to help them know how to properly behave.

Puppy adoption fees are $450, which includes the following: ($354 at the time of adoption)
Spay/Neuter
Rabies
1st Set of puppy shots
2nd set of puppy shots
3rd set of puppy shots
microchip
deworm
2 free vet visits

For adult dogs, WE WILL BE HOLDING ADOPTIONS ON SATURDAYS & SUNDAYS FROM 10-4 PM at our Adoption Center. No appointments necessary.  

A Path 4 Paws holds adoption events at our Adoptions Store,  located at 232 N. Jones Blvd, Suite 170  right next to CAL Ranch (North Jones/ I-95).   Please bring your dog(s) for a meet and greet (if applicable)  Please bring your entire family so everyone can meet. 

If you are interested in Olympus, please contact dogrescuelv@hotmail.com to confirm the dog you are interested in,  will be attending that particular event.  We have limited space at the store, therefore we can not take every dog out to the event.

Olympus is spayed/neutered, has current vaccinations and includes a microchip, deworming and 2 free vet visits.  Adoption fee applies.  Please make sure you have read the information listed on the homepage for requirements and restrictions. 

Foster homes & volunteers are always needed.  Please contact us regarding how you can help by fostering or volunteering for our organization.

animal.description:
Meet Gentle! He is a 2 year old that was rescued from a meat farm in South Korea. We have partners we work with there that pull these dogs from the worst horrors imaginable before they are set to be on someone's dinner plate.
Many of these dogs start off in horrific puppy mill type facilities on tiny rabbit cage size wire crates in complete filth. If they are not sold at 6 or 8 weeks then they either stay for a couple years to be used to breed more and then are sold off to the meat trade, or they are sold off right away. South Korea is one of the only countries that actually farms dogs for their meat. Little dogs are used for elixirs and potions.
Gentle is very sweet! Gentle and several of his friends have been flown here for a chance at a future and a real life. Our adoption fee is $600 which helps offset some of the flight costs. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an online application form at https://form.jotform.com/oscarlucy/dog-adoption-app

By providing them with socialization and obedience training as puppies can also make them easier to handle as adults, as shar-peis are strong-willed dogs whose personalities may overwhelm an unprepared pet parent. These dogs do best with confident, assertive leadership to help them know how to properly behave.

Puppy adoption fees are $450, which includes the following: ($354 at the time of adoption)
Spay/Neuter
Rabies
1st Set of puppy shots
2nd set of puppy shots
3rd set of puppy shots
microchip
deworm
2 free vet visits

For adult dogs, WE WILL BE HOLDING ADOPTIONS ON SATURDAYS & SUNDAYS FROM 10-4 PM at our Adoption Center. No appointments necessary.  

A Path 4 Paws holds adoption events at our Adoptions Store,  located at 232 N. Jones Blvd, Suite 170  right next to CAL Ranch (North Jones/ I-95).   Please bring your dog(s) for a meet and greet (if applicable)  Please bring your entire family so everyone can meet. 

If you are interested in Avalon, please contact dogrescuelv@hotmail.com to confirm the dog you are interested in,  will be attending that particular event.  We have limited space at the store, therefore we can not take every dog out to the event.

Avalon is spayed/neutered, has current vaccinations and includes a microchip, deworming and 2 free vet visits.  Adoption fee applies.  Please make sure you have read the information listed on the homepage for requirements and restrictions. 

Foster homes & volunteers are always needed.  Please contact us regarding how you can help by fostering or volunteering for our organization.

animal.description:
Boom! Boom! Boom! Earthquake!! Oh, wait. That's just me! Ya see- when I'm happy my whole body shakes from tip to tail! Nice to meet you! My name is Boomerang, and I am the happiest boy in the whole, wide world. Just hearing someone's voice sets off my wiggly dance. My ideal forever home is a home filled with snuggles, scratchies, and lots of couch time. Couch time is my favorite, especially when you let me snuggle up as close as I possibly can. Ya see- I haven't always had the best of luck in my past and the result is my back leg is a littlewonky. I can still get around well- even run- but my gait is just a little different. My foster family says it just adds to my character and uniqueness. My boots also make me unique. Sometimes I wear magical booties on my back feeties so I don't slip on hardwood floors. They make me more confident and help me on stairs, too. My foster family has had dozens of foster dogs and they've never quite had a foster as "sweet and wonderful" as I am. That makes me proud! I don't know many fancy tricks, but I am very well mannered. I would love to be a part of a family with kids or other dogs. Other dogs help me feel comfortable and are good snuggle stand ins until I can plop down with my beloved humans. If you are looking for a low key, extremely loveable new member of your family- I am your boy! Let's be best friends forever!

If you are interested in adopting Boomerang, please fill out an adoption application on our website at www.underhoundrailroad.org. Boomerang is currently being fostered in North Carolina is by transport North to his furever home beginning in late February.

animal.description:
Annika, Grass Valley
Contact: caindenise@gmail.com
Home2Home-Nc adoption assistance

Female, 7 yr, spayed and shots
70 lbs, medium height
Very friendly to all, well socialized 
Avid car traveler (no back of truck travel)
Welcome in any home or business
Playful like a puppy
Strong and healthy
Breed: Bull terrier/Staffy mix
Beautiful brindle/gray coloring

I cannot rave about Annika enough. If you have been looking for a dog that is mature, but fun loving and full of great energy, Annika is the girl for you. Very affectionate too.

Annika was raised from a tiny pup by a single man. She was with him 24/7, until he passed away Halloween 2020. Annika fell into deep depression and quit eating, she missed him so much. She was his car buddy, hardware store, auto store buddy. He built her a special seat in his van so she could watch the world go by on their many days out looking for car parts. She laid at his feet when he wrenched on his cars. Nothing was too good for his special girl! Annika thrives on love and attention.

Annika has recovered from her sadness, and is ready to live and love again! She has many family visitors, but none can add her to their homes. Soon her house will be sold, so it is time! Annika is an indoor girl. Does not like being out in the cold.

Annika would do great with a couple. Older kids and visitors are fine with this friendly girl. She does take her job as head squirrel chaser serious, so maybe no scaredy-cat. A cat that won’t run is probably ok. A 4’ fence keeps her safely in yard. She will not run away. She adores family and will stay close even off leash. Dad taught her many good manners.

If you feel you can give Annika the perfect forever home, please contact us. Home check and modest Sr adoption fee.

Caindenises@gmail.com
Grass Valley, Ca

animal.description: Meet Sirine! She is an adorable loving 5 year old that was rescued off the streets of Thailand after being dumped. Many expats (non Thai residents), spend half the year in Thailand and wind up adopting dogs while they are there. When it's time to go back to their own country, they leave the dogs on the road. Only a handful will ever survive this life. Sirine is one of the very lucky ones. She was found and taken to a vet clinic, where sadly she then lived in a cage for a year. One of the rescuers we work with was finally able to get her from this clinic and take her to her home before she could be ready to fly. On January 29th, she made her freedom flight to Los Angeles to search for a new future and a life she once only dreamed possible. She is a gentle sweet soul that would prefer to be in your arms and on your lap as much as possible. She is a sweet adorable girl who is ready for her new chance and to only be spoiled and pampered for the rest of her life. Our adoption fee is $600 which helps offset some of the flight costs. If you are interested in adopting, please go to our website and fill out an online application form. https://form.jotform.com/oscarlucy/dog-adoption-app

animal.description:
Please call the shelter at (706) 795-2868 to schedule a meet and greet.

Madison Oglethorpe Animal Shelter is a non-profit shelter serving over 720 square miles. We are open intake, meaning we can not turn away animals from either county we serve. Our shelter intakes double or triple it's capacity every month so it is essential we place animals quickly into adoptive homes. Since so many animals enter the shelter we often don't have enough volunteers to write an individual bio for each. Please feel free to call the shelter Wednesday-Sunday to inquire about the animal you are interested in. 706-795-2868.

Viewing and adoption hours at our shelter are Wednesday through Sunday from 12 PM to 5 PM. 
All adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, flea treatment, deworming, and spay or neuter, microchip, and adoption packet. 
Fees:
Dogs over 4 months old: $100
Puppies under 4 months: $125. 
Cats and Kittens are $75 ($65 without microchip). 

For your convenience you can fill out an adoption application for any of our current residents at www.moaspets.com. Join us on Facebook at
https://www.facebook.com/moaspets. It's a great way to stay up to the minute on the furry 4 legged friends we have looking for a loving forever home. 
We are located at:
1888 Colbert Danielsville Rd 
Danielsville, GA 30633 
706-795-2868

NOTE: Our adoptions are first come first served, simply filling out an application does not mean the animal will be held for you, you must come meet the animal in person in order to be considered for adoption.
If you rent you must bring your lease or a letter from your landlord stating you may adopt.

animal.description:
Sweet Lily lost her family when her dad had to go into assisted living and wasn't able to take her. She was in boarding with our boarding partner for a couple months while he was in and out of the hospital. Once he realized he wasn't going to be able to continue to care for her, he surrendered her in hopes of Lily finding a wonderful and loving home for her golden years. Lily is an easygoing girl who would love a big, soft bed and a few treats now and then. She doesn't ask for much and promises to be a very good girl.
We are looking for a foster or forever home for Lily.


ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.tinyurl.com/IADRAdoptionApp

If you'd like to help Lily while she searches for her very own family, you can sponsor her for only $19/month here: https://petbucks.org/pet/6222/sponsor/create


***IMPORTANT- PLEASE READ***
The State of Texas requires rescues to collect sales tax on any adoption fees. Our adoption fee is $175. Texas State Sales Tax will be added to that amount.

Due to the nature of our adoption process, our fosters are usually only able to consider potential adopters within the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex. A vet reference is required, and a trial period will be completed before finalizing the adoption. Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
**If you are interested in Lala, please fill out an adoption application on our website: www.roversretreat.org**

Meet Lala, our beautiful 4 year old Golden Retriever. This sweet girl was discarded by her family in Turkey when one of the family members became allergic to dogs. Lucky for Lala she was taken care of by our rescuer until she was able to fly to the US in mid January. After arriving, Lala adjusted immediately to the good life with her foster family and doggie foster sister.

She has LOTS of energy and wants to be anywhere her humans are. She is definitely the epitome of a velcro doggie. The only time she isn’t sitting at your side is when she is playing with a toy or ball. Lala is very smart and is doing great with her basic commands.  She sits when told and is learning to come when called. She mastered the doggy door quickly and knows to go to the bathroom outside. As with any rescued dog, Lala will need to be shown the appropriate place to go potty at her forever home and receive praise and treats for going there. 

Lala is very good on the leash and only pulls when she is excited. She is sweet with other dogs, and is happy to socialize, but she is more interested in attention from humans than from other dogs. She is currently getting 2-3 walks a day, and continuing her daily walking routine will be important to keep her energy in check. Lala would do great in a home with a large yard for her to play fetch in. Lala is quite agile, and if given the opportunity she can jump a 5’+ fence...especially if her people are on the other side. A secure yard with supervised access will be important in her future home. 

LaLa loves sleeping on the bed as close to her humans as possible and will cuddle with you all night. She is eager to try to jump up on the couch to join her humans, so a family who is looking for a cuddle buddy would be a good fit for Lala. 

Lala has a sweet personality and is so lovable. She is great with new people and wants all the scratches and belly rubs she can get. She will do well with a family that can give her love and attention all day and plenty of exercise.

If Lala sounds like she might be a good fit for your family, please complete an adoption application on our website: www.roversretreat.org

NOTE: due to the high cost of international transportation, Lala’s adoption fee is $1,000

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR A NEW BEST FRIEND?

Check out Snoozer:

With his gorgeous, black lined, super expressive bedroom eyes, his awesome friendly personality and his easy to get along with nature, Snoozer is a rare gem, when it comes to rescue dogs.

That is why we are still scratching our heads, over how he came to be with us.

Can you believe this guy got tossed out of a truck, that then took off, with 
Snoozer in full on pursuit,until he just couldn't go anymore???

WE CAN'T EITHER.

Not that dumping a dog in this fashion is EVER ok but we keep waiting to see some difficult or annoying behavior that might have led to someone doing such a thing...and so far, there just aren't any.  He is a super cool guy.

So let's get down to it.  We named him Snoozer because one of our volunteers lives in the area Snoozer was abandoned.  Witnesses had seen him get dumped and the next day, our volunteer just happened to see Snoozer walking by her house.  What could she do?  She opened the door and invited him in and he was only too happy to make himself at home, where he laid down and slept for most of the rest of the day, exhausted from his ordeal.

So we named him Snoozer.

But he's not a fuddy-duddy, couch potato.  While he does indeed, enjoy his couch time and bed time and nap time and movie time, he's got great energy and ability to go on hikes, walks, adventures, car rides, road trips, you name it.  Snoozers down.  That is why he likes his naps.  You just never know when you might need to expend all that saved up energy.

Snoozer is about 2-3 years old, judging by his teeth and weighed in at 29lbs.  He is in good weight and done growing so you can count on him to stay this size throughout his life, unless you treat too often or feed too much.  We think he is probably a mix of beagle and lab with some terrier of some sort thrown in to lift those ears up a bit but whatever it is, it came together to make a perfectly sized, perfectly handsome, very affectionate and easy going, all around, good guy.

Snoozer does fine on a leash, lives happily with an array of dog genders and sizes, does fine with the cats in the home and has had minimal potty accidents, though we would hesitate to call him 100% housebroken.  He will bark at passing dogs but is not a loud or nuisance barker.  He travels well in a car, loves people of all kinds so bring on the family.  We have not tested him with toddlers or infants but humans six and over, will be adored.

So if you have been looking for a new BFF, partner in crime, side kick extraordinaire, look no further.  Snoozer is your guy and he is going to make some lucky person, couple or family, an amazing companion.

If you would like to meet this amazing little dude, please go to our website at www.allmuttsgreatandsmall.org/adoption and submit the adoption application.  If approved, well make arrangements for you to come meet him, to see if there's a spark.

Snoozer is neutered, microchipped, has had his rabies vaccination and is up to date on his five way vaccinations.  He has been fecal checked and treated for internal bugs and treated for external ones.  All he needs is the promise of forever.  He would like to be sure that when he gets in a car or a truck for a fun ride, that is what he will get, and then be brought back home to share the couch, a good movie and a box of Cheese-Nips.

His adoption fee is $275

Please note:

*Inquiries submitted through Petfinder, are not the same as applications 
  submitted through our webpage.  
*Yes we do out of state adoptions.
*No, we do not transport. You must be willing to come and meet the dog and 
  take it home with you.
*Yes we do Canadian adoptions.
*If the dog is on Petfinder, it is still available.
*You must be 18 years of age to adopt
*If you submit questions about an adoptable dog, covered in the Petfinder bio, 
 we will not respond.
*We do not pick the first good application.  We pick the most suitable 
  application for the dog, out of all submitted.
*All correspondence is handled via email as time allows.  
* If you are not chosen, you will not be notified

For a more detailed explanation of our adoption process, go to www.allmuttsgreatandsmall.org/adoption and read "The Adoption Process" link

animal.description:
About one year old and 35 lbs, Erwin is a fun happy young fella that is a perfect size for cuddles and travel, but not too small to miss out on more active adventures. He may have a little bit of growing left to do, but unlikely too much more if any at all. He's got long legs that would be perfect for running or climbing up onto your lap to snuggle. Still being young, Erwin would surely benefit from a home interested in giving him some proper guidance and structure to mold him into the ideal adult dog, a path he is well on his way down! He is quiet and sleeps well in his crate, gets along well with other dogs, and is adorably affectionate with volunteers. He will go to the door to signal he needs to go potty and walks well on a leash. If you'd like to meet Erwin, don't delay in getting in your adoption request!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
*INQUIRIES SENT THROUGH PETFINDER WILL NOT BE ANSWERED AS WE DO NOT HAVE THE MANPOWER TO RESPOND TO THEM. PLEASE COMPLETE OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTEAD*

Meet Sensational Sophie-NC!

Sophie is in an IDOG foster home in Gastonia-NC. Please read ALL the information in her listing before applying for her. If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for her, please complete our adoption application at http://www.idogrescue.com/adoption_application 
(copy/paste the URL into your browser). 

If you have completed an application in the last 3 months and meet the requirements for his new home, you can email us at rescue@idogrescue.com and let us know you are interested in Sophie.

We will review your application and let you know if you made our short list of applicants. We base our adoption decisions on what is in the best interest of our dogs. Please note our adoption policies are in place for the safety and welfare of our dogs - your understanding is appreciated.

We are all volunteers and have jobs, families, pets of our own to care for - we do the best that we can to get back to you in a timely manner. We believe in taking time to go through our thorough process to try to match the dog with the best fit for that dog.

Our adoption process may take 2-4 weeks:
• You must be approved to adopt before we will schedule a meet and greet.
• We expect approved adopters to visit her in her foster home within a short period of time of being approved to adopt her.
• Our adoption process involves vet and personal reference checks, phone interviews, a home visit, an adoption contract and an adoption fee.

*AGE: 15 months (born October 2019)

*WEIGHT: 59 lbs.

*FENCE REQUIREMENT: A physical secure fence is required. No electronic fence or e-collar will be allowed as we feel this would not set her up for success.

*COAT TYPE: Long straight moderate shedding coat. Her new family should be prepared to brush her daily and have her groomed every 6-8 weeks. This is approximately $100 per groom.

*ENERGY LEVEL: high puppy. When she first sees you, she gets really excited but calms down very quickly.  She will need daily exercise, socialization and training to work on manners.

*DOGS: She has lived with a dog her whole life so she may do best in a home with another dog. She does well with other dogs and would do well with a patient dog who can tolerate her puppy antics.  

*CATS: unknown. She has had no exposure. 

*KIDS: 8+. Her prior owner told us she does great with children but may jump on young children and accidentally knock them down.

*CAR: will get car sick if she eats right before going in car. Otherwise she rides in the car very well.

*CRATE: she will go in crate at night when you are home with no issues. Does not enjoy crate if left alone and will destroy the crate.  She is in crate at night for about 8-9 hours with no issues.  She has been left alone for about 6-8 hours in the house with no issues although she would much rather be next to you than in the crate. 

*HOUSE TRAINED: yes!

*LEASH: Sophie likes going for walks and needs more training on leash to walk loosely.

Here's what Sophie’s foster parent has to say about her:

Sophie is a 15 month old 59 lb. female Goldendoodle who was surrendered to IDOG by her family who wanted her to get more attention and exercise than they were able to provide. 

Are you looking for a Valentine that sticks to you like Velcro and follows you everywhere?  Then Sophie is your gal! 

Sophie is sweet like honey, fun-loving, and her personality shines!  Sophie needs a home with a fenced yard and family that will be home the majority of the day or one she can be with. Sophie spent the majority of her day in her prior home living outside during the day so inside living is a whole new world for Sophie and she is thriving.

She has some separation anxiety and would do better in a home where humans are home regularly or she can go with them. Sophie is a young pup who wants to please!  She loves attention and giving hugs and is a great companion. Her temperament is very sweet, loving, gentle, and playful.  She is skittish and a bit fearful in new situations and will need patience and continued training and socialization. She is still a puppy so she should learn quickly.  

The ideal home for Sophie is one where someone is home most of the day as she would much rather be next you than in a crate.  She will follow you around everywhere and lay right next to you.  She likes to play fetch and go on walks.  She will need someone who is patient and willing to work with her on socialization and manners. She is a bit slow to warm up to people and may growl initially due to her lack of socialization but does warm up. She has shown no aggression whatsoever. 

She would do well in a home with another dog that is patient. She has always had another dog in her home so would likely be more successful in a home with another dog.  She needs daily exercise to keep her energy at a good level.  

She loves tennis balls, tug-o-war, ice, frisbee, Benebones. She also has gone hiking with her foster and loved it.

Sophie is spayed, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, and house trained. She is heartworm and fecal negative and on heartworm/flea and tick preventatives.

ADOPTION FEE: $495

OUR ADOPTION FEES RANGE FROM $100 - $750 depending on the dog. The following is a general guide, but each dog is assessed individually. It currently costs IDOG an average of over $400 for basic vet, grooming, and foster care on each dog; that does not allow for the ones who get sick, need surgery, have special needs, or are heartworm positive.

ADOPTION FEES:
Under 6 months $550 and up
6 months to 2 years $450 and up
2 years - 4 years $350 and up
4 years + $100 and up
Special Needs fee/donation assessed on individual basis

TO APPLY FOR THIS DOG, PLEASE COMPLETE THE APPLICATION ON OUR WEBSITE:
http://www.idogrescue.com/adoption_application

animal.description: This puppy is one of 7 from Stockton Missouri .  The mother is a 50 to 60 pound black lab looking dog.  She is a great mom and super sweet.  This puppy is one of 5 frodm the litter and we will get the last 2 fixed from the litter hopefully on Monday.  Our adoption fee includes his neutering which was done, a vet exam with a fecal check, puppies first series of his DA2PPV, his bordetella vaccination, his first  series of his Canine Combo Influenza H3N2 and H3N8 , deworming , a package of free doggie day camp , grooming and a dog training consultation once a month for 4 months. You'll also receive anytime in the first year of your adoption at the same place a full day of doggie day camp, one free night boarding  , a bath or grooming and a coupon for dog training , a bag of dental dog bones, a doggie toothbrush, 2 free bags of puppy food, 2 months of flea and tick preventatives', one month of a heartworm preventative, a great coupon booklet you can use at any that has many money saving coupons off your puppy supplies at any Petsmart store plus the booklet offers a free hotel stay at any of the Petsmart that have a hotel, a 30 minute dog training consultation , a free day of doggie day camp and there is a coupon for Banfield to have a free vet exam .  The rescue group had the vet put a microchip in the puppy at the time if neuter.  The microchip company offers the adopter a free 30 day health insurance offer that you can activate if you want health insurance for your puppy .  You'll also get the puppies microchip tag and the puppies rescue group tag.   If you'd like to do a meet and greet  with this puppy you can call Ken at 636-388-1636 to schedule a appointment,  Puppies are shown by appointment only.
