animal.description:
Meet Bailey ~

My name is  Bailey and I am a Boxer mix from South Carolina. I weigh roughly 40lbs.
Rescued from a shelter then adopted out, I am again, in need of a home. It seems like I was just too big or just too energetic for my adopters so they didn't want me anymore! 
I am a nice girl for sure! Being kind and friendly to other dogs and humans, I have a very soft way about me. 

 With my adorable looks, and unbridled loyalty, I will always be there for you through thick and thin. I will never judge you, or turn my back on you. Every single day, you will look at me and you will know that you are loved unconditionally. I will never betray you or hurt you, and I will grow old by your side.

******IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ ALL THE GREAT INFO BELOW******

***Please don't apply unless you are very serious about adopting, and are ready to move forward with the adoption process. We are super busy and make a great effort to respond back to EVERYONE ASAP! WHEN WE TAKE THE TIME TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION AND RESPOND BACK TO THE APPLICANT JUST TO BE EITHER IGNORED OR BE TOLD THEY CANNOT COME FOR SEVERAL DAYS, MORE TIME IS WASTED~PLEASE HAVE MORE RESPECT THAN THAT!

PLEASE read our website's ADOPTION PROCESS PAGE prior to submitting an adoption application. www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-process 
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-application 

ABOUT OUR RESCUE DOGS: 
 All of our dogs are located in Connecticut, are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, have been given deworming medications, and have had CT State health checks, & go home with a leash, collar, & packet of medical paperwork. 

BREED IDENTIFICATION:
Please understand that many rescue dogs are mixes of multiple breeds. Petfinder allows us to choose up to two breeds per dog. While the shelters and our rescue do our best in accurately identifying breeds, breed identification is not guaranteed. If there is a certain breed that you do not want, it is very important that you share this with our rescue when applying. When adopting a puppy, breed uncertainty plays a big part in the size/look of the dog as an adult. Please know that any puppy can be a wonderful dog, regardless of preconceived notions of certain breeds, but it is very important that the adopter has the dedication and patience to raise the puppy with boundaries, consistency, structure, & love. The more effort you give towards training & time you allow for exercise, your puppy will grow to be a HUGE source of UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, TOTAL LOYALTY, HAPPINESS, COMFORT & COMPANIONSHIP!

ABOUT OUR RESCUE:
We are a small rescue run by volunteers & focused on finding the right match for both our dogs & for you. If you are interested in adopting through our rescue, you first will need to complete an adoption application & be approved as a potential adopter before meeting any of our pups. No need to be intimidated by our application as it allows us to get to know you & your lifestyle. Of course, the more you can share the better! Please also note, while a fenced yard is fantastic, it is not required by our rescue, however, it may be required for a certain dog occasionally.  Once adoption applicants are approved to become potential adopters, we offer private appointments where you can meet one or several dogs at the discretion of the rescue. We offer a unique & pleasant experience focused on finding the perfect match. It is extremely important to us that everyone is treated with respect & that NO ONE IS LEFT HANGING. WE WILL GET BACK TO YOU WITHIN 2 TO 3 DAYS of application submission. If there is a dog you are eager to meet, please  TEXT US DIRECTLY at 203-241-2351 so that we can check the status of your application and move it forward immediately. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new best friend.

*All adult dogs can be cat tested by request.

HOME/RENTER INSURANCE:
SOME PROVIDERS HAVE VERY STRICT POLICIES REGARDING WHICH TYPE OF DOG BREEDS ARE ALLOWED UNDER THEIR COVERAGE. STATE FARM WAS SUGGESTED TO US AS THEY DO NOT PUNISH, DROP, NOR REFUSE YOU DUE TO DOG BREED SHOULD YOU RUN INTO ISSUES WITH YOUR CURRENT PROVIDER.

animal.description:
AO52984 Kaiser,  German Shepherd dog, neutered male, est. 2 years, 85  pounds - available for adoption now.

Contact : Calaveras County Animal Services (209) 754-6509

or Kbandy@co.calaveras.ca.us or svavzincak@co.calaveras.ca.us   

Kaiser may have been tied up- he arrived with a chewed off rope attached to his choke chain.

Initially he was was growly in his kennel. We won him over with treats he took with a soft mouth.  He loves peanut butter Kongs.

Kaiser turned out to be a playful gentle giant who now barks for attention.

He chases and juggles the ball.

Kaiser has just had a week of  training with Margaret Blair at Twin Cedars Canine.

He  knows or has been introduced to: loose lead, heel, auto sit, down, stay and come.

He waits for his food and doorways. Without distractions he is good for all.

Kaiser’s "big issue" is that he escapes his fence; he does not like to be confined.

Her becomes overstimulated and reactive when he sees other dogs; 

per Margaret, his behavior around other dogs appears to be excitement.

If you have another dog, a “meet ’n greet" is required.

Due to his size, older children would be best.

This very affectionate boy loves people and is eager to go home with you now.

animal.description:
Quinn (the mom) and her litter of pups arrived in our care when the pups were less than 10 days old.  The litter is now 8 weeks old and the pups are ready for adoption.  We do not know their actual breed mix but mom has a shepherd appearance.  They are likely mixed with several breeds and will be at least medium when full grown.  Some could end up larger though.  Its hard for us to know at this age.  They are active pups and will need active homes with plenty of time for outside exercise and play time.  They will also benefit from obedience training so they can be the best companions ever.  

Please do breed research before adopting any pup - make sure your type of home and lifestyle is the right fit for the activity level and needs of the particular breeds mentioned as a possible mix in our rescue pups.  Keep in mind though that we can only guess the breed(s) we think we see in the pups we rescue.   Without knowing the background information on them and exactly what breed(s) their parents are, its just an educated guess on our parts.

Our puppy adoption fee is $150.00 each and our pups have been spayed/neutered, wormed, vaccinated for kennel cough and have received their first parvo/distemper shot. We require a fenced yard or if you live in the country safe acreage on your own land for exercise. Our dogs must be allowed in their family home and be allowed to sleep inside of the home at night. At adoption you will be required to complete and sign an adoption contract. 

We are located in Billings, Montana and require adopters to travel to our location.  

If you would like to inquire about adopting this pup or have questions, please contact foster mom Stacee at 406-208-3853.

animal.description:
Rescued: 8/27/2020
Age at the time of rescue: 6 weeks
Current weight: 24 pounds

Peso and his three siblings were born on historical tribal land on the island of Puerto Rico. They are all very sweet and loving. Typical Labrador behavior and in search of forever homes. If you'd like to apply to adopt Peso, please log onto www.scarpr.org and click on How to Adopt. His adoption fee is $425 which includes transportation off the island of Puerto Rico, full vaccinations and sterilization. Due to flight limitations, we are looking for homes in the upper East Coast and Minnesota area at this time. Thank you for your support of our mission to save lives. www.scarpr.org

Quinn (the mom) and her litter of pups arrived in our care when the pups were less than 10 days old.  The litter is now 8 weeks old and the pups are ready for adoption.  We do not know their actual breed mix but mom has a shepherd appearance.  They are likely mixed with several breeds and will be at least medium when full grown.  Some could end up larger though.  Its hard for us to know at this age.  They are active pups and will need active homes with plenty of time for outside exercise and play time.  They will also benefit from obedience training so they can be the best companions ever.  

Please do breed research before adopting any pup - make sure your type of home and lifestyle is the right fit for the activity level and needs of the particular breeds mentioned as a possible mix in our rescue pups.  Keep in mind though that we can only guess the breed(s) we think we see in the pups we rescue.   Without knowing the background information on them and exactly what breed(s) their parents are, its just an educated guess on our parts.

Our puppy adoption fee is $150.00 each and our pups have been spayed/neutered, wormed, vaccinated for kennel cough and have received their first parvo/distemper shot. We require a fenced yard or if you live in the country safe acreage on your own land for exercise. Our dogs must be allowed in their family home and be allowed to sleep inside of the home at night. At adoption you will be required to complete and sign an adoption contract. 

We are located in Billings, Montana and require adopters to travel to our location.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Are you looking for an older dog to keep you company and watch tv with, then I'm your guy. I'm a special needs kind of guy, because I can't see, and I have urinary issues. I do let you know when I have to potty but can't always make it out the door. I will have to always have a belly band on so I don't wet on the floor. I can't see so I need to be in a home with adult and/or older children. I currently live with two cats, they don't hang around me too much and we get along fine. I do great in the the car, and on a leash. At night I like to snuggle up either under the covers or on top. I also like to bury my nose in the covers while sleeping, my foster family thinks it's adorable. They say I'm a good boy and well behaved. I do have some anxiety but that comes with my breed. My medication helps me out. I cry/whimper when I'm hungry or need to go potty. I recently had a dental and had a lot of teeth removed. My mouth feels better and my breath is better, but I will need to be on soft food. If you are interested in meeting me go to www.adopthope.org and my foster mom will get in touch with you. Chico's adoption fee is $200 and includes his neuter, microchip and current vaccinations and preventatives plus a free basic obedience course at Cedar Run Pet Boarding in Hiawatha. Last Hope requires that all animals be kept as indoor pets only, be altered and current on vaccinations and preventatives. Our adoption process includes reference and background checks, a vet check and a home visit.

animal.description:
Zina. Zina is a German Shepherd/Hound mix, one year-old, and spayed. She is loving, snuggly, loyal, smart, playful, and highly active. She makes a great guard dog and will flourish in a home with ROOM to run:  a big yard, near the woods, etc.  After a long walk, she settles down fine the rest of the day, and she loves to cuddle up on the couch. 
Zina gets along with other dogs after calm introductions. She has never met a cat, but definitely seems like she wants to chase them, so a cat-free home would probably be best. She has been exposed to a few children, but perhaps a home with older or no children might be better. But she is very friendly and curious, so could be adaptable. 
Some of her challenging traits are that, as a guard dog, she barks and gets excited with postmen, visitors, etc. She is excitable on walks, wanting to hunt, smell, and meet other dogs. Although she is 50#, she seems to have the energy and strength of an 80# dog! She's a pistol.
She'll thrive in a home with a patient assertive owner who is dedicated to training her, exercising her regularly, and wanting a protective loyal companion.
If you or someone you know are looking for a high energy dog with lots of love and loyalty to give, Zina may be your pup contact adalovesdogs@gmail.com

animal.description:
Sweet and Shy but she will be your new BFF!Nessy is a sweet girl that came to AC PAW after living for weeks in her owner's car with her sister, Harley. As a result of living this life, she is shy when she first meets new humans and dogs. But once she is comfortable, she is the sweetest thing ever and loves to snuggle.
Nessy is playful and wants to be with her humans but she does okay when left alone too - she says just don't leave me alone for long, I want to be included in the fun!
Nessy is good with other dogs, kids and adults! We don't know about cats. Due to being left alone in a car for long periods of time (including during very cold weather), Nessy was a bit behind in understanding what housetraining is all about, but she is smart and working on learning with the help of her foster family. Her new family will need to continue that work to help her succeed.
As with all AC PAW pets, Nessy is spayed, fully vaccinated, microchipped and certified fully lovable! If you are interested in being considered for Nessy, please fill out our pre-adoption form at: https://acpaw.wufoo.com/forms/q18s4vtj0jnnt1t/
If you are interested in adopting this AC PAW pet or would like to set up a meet-and-greet please fill out our pre-adoption questionnaire at acpaw.org.

animal.description:
Tierney is a sweet easy-going adult hound about 45 lbs. She gets along just fine with dogs of all sizes on the farm but isn't necessarily looking for a playmate. She would love to find a home with a fenced yard where she can lounge in a sunbeam and sniff all the smells 'till her heart's content. She's not high maintenance in the slightest and it won't take much more than some head scratches and yummy treats to make her tail wag. Tierney is truly just the sweetest hound dog and will make a wonderful buddy for some lucky someone. Get in your application to meet this sweet girl!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description: Hi folks! My name is Dean (HWTH#21031A). I am a Shepherd mix, born 5/20/20 and I weigh 57 lbs. I was found as a stray in Rosamond by a Good Samaritan. My owner never claimed me so I was relinquished to Halfway to Home so I could be adopted by my forever family. I am a sweet, friendly and playful boy who walks well on a leash. My ideal owners will be active people who take part in outdoor adventures like jogging, hiking, and camping. I am still a pup so it is important that I receive house- and obedience-training to help me learn proper behavior and to help me bond with you. A home with a fenced-yard where I can safely run around and play is essential. When I'm done exercising for the day, I want to be in the house where I am treated like part of the family. I don't know how I will do with other dogs, cats, or children so when we meet we can find out together. I am confident I will make a loving and loyal companion. If you would like to find out more information about me, or would like to make an appointment to meet me, please call Sandy at tele# 661-824-4495 (landline). Thanks for reading, see you soon!

animal.description:
Meet Shooby! Shooby is a goofy 3 year old Pit-Mix snuggle bug. When he is not cuddling, he loves to play chase, tug, and chew on his toys. Shobby also loves to run free, so his ideal forever home would have a fenced in backyard for his zoomies. Shooby loves his foster fur sister and parents, but he is scared of new things, people, and animals, so he needs to take new introductions very slowly. While Shooby loves the people he knows and his fur foster sibling, Shooby does best with a routine and around people that can read his cues and give him space when he asks for it. Because of this, we recommend that he is adopted to a home that has another dog and kids 15 and up. Shooby is particularly nervous of new things when on leash, so a home with a fenced yard where he does not need to be walked often is a requirement. He may take some time to trust you, but once he does he quickly makes up for the wait with love and laughs!

The adoption donation for Shooby is $300.  This donation helps to cover veterinary expenses including spay/neuter, microchip and vaccinations.

Wish Upon a Rescue is a 501(c)3 non-profit, foster based animal rescue. If you would like to meet Shooby, please complete our adoption questionnaire at www.wishuponarescue.org/adopt. We will review your responses and be in contact to schedule a meet and greet at a time and place convenient for your family and our team members.

animal.description:
So today is Bobby's big debut as an available guy. He has came so far since Sunday. While his past has been unthinkable for most of us, his has a bright future ahead of him. He is about 7 yrs old. He is a mixed breed rescue. He is not very big, probably 25-30 pounds. He is up to date on shot and microchipped. He is not neutered so there is a $100 refundable deposit that is returned when he is neutered. He loves everyone he meets. A little shy at first but warms up very fast. Sometimes he loves a little too much so probably best with older kids because he just doesn’t understand gentle yet. He has not met any kids here so not sure about smaller humans. He has never had an accident since he has been here. He does very good inside but loves it outdoors. Bobby has been good with our small dogs and the cat. We will miss him dearly when he leaves but very excited for his future. His adoption fee is $250 which is being sponsored in honor of our much loved and lost way too soon, baby Belle. Reminder He is not neutered so there is a $100 refundable deposit that is returned when he is neutered.
He is being fostered in Tomah WI
Apply for him at www.lastpawrescue.org
“501(c) 3 approved WI Agriculture license number 285589-DS”

animal.description:
BELL is a 2 yr old female terrier mix. She is UTD on vaccinations & microchipped. She is waiting for her spay appointment. She weighs around 8lbs.

Bell was an amazing mama to her 6 puppies but she is ready to be a dog & enjoy her life! She has the CUTEST smile when she is excited & does a little dance. She loves being held & will roll over for belly rubs! She is also independent & will keep herself busy. She loves to follow you around & will seriously melt in your arms. She will need continued leash/harness training. She is working on potty training. She gets along with other dogs, men, women & kids. We are unsure about cats.

She is available through our "Pathway to Home" program. Please complete an adoption application at www.pathwaysforpaws.com if Bell is the missing piece to your family!

animal.description:
Is Thor still available?? 

(Unfortunately, we will not reply to emails asking this question as we do not have the time or volunteers to do so. We update our website daily just so you will know the status right away).  PLEASE GO TO OUR WEBSITE for up to date information to find out.  Check the Gallery by putting your mouse on the photo. 
IF it says Pending, we chose someone, but they haven't met up yet.  If it says Adopted, then the dog has been happily united with a forever family.  IF nothing is there other than their name, they are still available.

APPLY if interested so you can be considered.?

*Our page is updated daily. Please go to www.wowdogrescue.org for any updates.

Thor is approx. 4 lb.  Most likely a Jack Russel/Chi/ and Maltese mix puppy.
(Basing this on what the other pups look like).  He was found in a box in an alley with 3 other puppies.  The lady that found them went door to door asking if they knew who these pups belonged too...but no one seemed to know. One neighbor wanted 1 of them and the 3 came to our rescue.  They are now 13 weeks old and are being vetted and spay/neutered.  Thor is scheduled for Feb 16th to be neutered.

Thor is a sweetheart., and he loves to cuddle. He knows when he gets his sweater on that it is time to go for a car ride, which he loves.

Thor is learning to play fetch with a tennis ball.  He is still working on being potty trained, so has a few accidents.

Thor has super soft fur, and about 1/" long.  ?Thor will follow you around and lay down where ever you are and if he cannot see you he is up looking for you.  Thor enjoys chewing on a bully stick and does fine in a large play Xpen during the day while the fosters are gone to work. Night time he sleeps in bed with the fosters.

Thor is eating solid food.

Thor will be neutered, puppy shot series, Bordetella and Microchipped by 2/16/21 Thor's adoption fee is set at $275.00

WE ARE NOT PETFINDER, WE ARE NOT ADOPTAPET OR RESCUE ME.  Our application is on our website:  www.wowdogrescue.org  ?**PLEASE do not call or email to see if he is "still" available.His Gallery photo on our website will be updated daily and will state his status.  IF we have chosen someone, he will be marked "Pending".  IF he has been adopted, he will be marked "Adopted".

***Tired of not finding, or not being chosen for the dog of your dream?? 
 Consider Fostering with us...Our Fosters have 1st chance at adopting the dog they foster, while we pay for everything.  Its a win win for both! YOU get to see if this is a good match for your family, while the dog is being loved in your home...

animal.description:
Oakley is an office type of guy. He loves to lay under your desk and on top of your feet!  He was found as a stray by animal control and was taken to the pound. . He is crate and house trained.   He walks well on a leash and is good with other dogs. He wants no confrontation with a grumpy dog and backs off but is always ready to rumble and play with his puppy dog pals. 

Oakley can sit and has great recall and loves to be by your side. His foster feels he will be a great off leash walking or hiking partner eventually after bonding with his new family. He is good with all ages but lots of little noisy kiddos screaming and running makes him nervous so a home with children 12 and older would be a better match. 

Oakley is 2 to 3 years old and is a Plott Hound mix and weighs 40 lbs.   He is neutered, micro-chipped and up to date on vaccines.   he is located in Houston, TX and will come to his new home on professional ground transport.   If you feel you could give Oakley a loving forever home please contact Freedom Street Rescue at rhondabarron@earthlink.net for an app or go online to www.freedomstreetrescue.org

animal.description:
Meet Sugar at Jefferson Feed, 4422 Jefferson Hwy., Jefferson LA 504-733-8572. E-mail cajunlassie78@att.net for an adoption application.

Meet Sugar! She is an 8 month old hound mix. Sugar is a little head shy at first but she's still learning to be a dog. Men make her a little nervous but eventually she warms up pretty quickly with the right introduction. Sugar has really bonded to some of her caretakers because they have given her the patience and love she really needs. She can be nervous around strangers but as soon as she sees someone she knows, she gets so excited. Could you be that person that Sugar can bond with?

One of the amazing staff members at Jefferson Feed is helping her learn basic obedience commands. She knows sit, down, kennel and is learning stay. She is also house broken. Sugar is good with other dogs but she tends to play a little rough since she's still learning the ropes of being a dog so a proper meet and greet will be needed if you have other dogs. She seems to chase the store cats so maybe a home without cats would be best. Her adoption fee is $67. She also tested negative for heartworms. Please email Martha, our dog adoption coordinator at cajunlassie78@att.net for an adoption application or more information about Sugar.

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE:  We do not adopt out on a first-come/first-serve basis.  Applications are accepted for a puppy and then a home check is scheduled.  If there are multiple applications for a puppy, after all home checks are done, then the puppy is adopted out to the home that is the best fit for that puppy.
***** All breeds listed are a best guess or based on information from our rescue partners and are not guaranteed*****
 
 ******Chicagoland Dog Rescue reserves the right to restrict adoption of a dog to potential adopters who live within a fifty (50) mile radius of Schaumburg, IL *****

Hello!!!! My name is Daisy and I am an energetic pup who loves lots of attention and plenty of play!  My ideal home would have lots of love to give, patience ‘cause I might make some mistakes and I am TEETHING, and time to work on training with me so I can be even more AMAZING!  I am crate trained and will go in with no problems at all AND I am almost totally housebroken, which is pretty good for someone as young as me!  Even being from the south has not stopped this girl from loving the snow.  AND toys!  Love toys!!!  And I have a turkey flavored bone which is pretty great,too!   But being young means I have lots to learn and keeping all four on the floor is one of those things!  If you would like to meet me, please fill out a pre adoption application and a CDR volunteer will get back to you just as quick as they can!
Tail wags and kisses-Daisy



**The ADOPTION FEE for this pet is $450 which includes getting the puppy/dog up to date on rabies, distemper and bordetella vaccines, fecal test and deworming if necessary, heartworm test, spay or neuter (not including pre-surgical bloodwork) and a microchip. Free access to our weekly training classes is also included for the life of the dog, something no other rescue in the area offers.***

animal.description:
Delphine is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet her.

Delphine is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~1 years 
Weight: ~51lbs (should gain some)
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes some time to settle, but overall doing well with her crate training
Dog sociability: Friendly with dogs on walks! Is eager to meet them and may pull to say 'hi!'
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Friendly with kids! Can be a little jumpy/excited when first greeting people. 
Ideal home: Delphine is a pretty adaptable gal! As an adolescent pup, she would like an adopter that is committed to working on training and helping her to exhaust her energy in positive ways.

Looking for the sweetest and most cuddly dog ever?!? You've found her with Delphine. She thinks she's a lap dog with the way she loves to cuddle with you. Delphine absolutely loves playing with other dogs and is super friendly with humans too! She is a huge fan of the belly rubs and getting all the pets. Take her out to your backyard or a nearby park and throw a tennis ball to see how fast she can run (you will be impressed!) Just don't ask her to bring the ball back - she hasn't mastered that part yet :)

Delphine's adoption fee is 300. She is spayed, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. She will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Nick is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Nick is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~2 years 
Weight: ~52lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Takes time to settle (10-30 minutes) and would benefit from continued training for this. 
Dog sociability: Reportedly dog-friendly and seems interested in saying 'hi!' when he sees dogs on walks - will pull to greet. 
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown but can be mouthy (play bites) and shy/timid, so recommended for teenagers only
Ideal home: Nick will prefer a home that can go slow with him as he is shy/timid of strangers at first, especially males. He is not a match for an elevator building or busy area, but is adaptable to other living environments. He has some good energy and would like an adopter that can continue to work on training and exhaust his energy in positive ways. 

Nick is a dreamboat who will charm you with his soft floppy ears and very boopable nose! He is such a quick learner and would thrive with someone who wants to teach him lots of commands and exercise with him regularly. Walkies are LIFE. He knows "sit" and "touch" and is so close to nailing "down." He really likes exploring and seems eager to meet dog friends along the way. While relaxing on the couch, Nick enjoys soft pets on his face and belly rubs, while being told he is the goodest most handsome pup in Chicagoland. 

Nick's adoption fee is 300. He will be neutered on a future date (3/11 at SNIP Society) and a 50 refundable neuter deposit will be required. He is up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Marcus is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Marcus is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~6 months
Weight: ~45lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! He needs to be on a strict schedule
Crate trained: Working on it! He takes some time to settle (10-30 minutes) and would benefit from continued training for this
Dog sociability: Reportedly dog-friendly, but we haven't seen him with dogs in our care yet.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but he is pretty mouthy (play bites) so only recommended for teenagers
Ideal home: Marcus is ALL PUPPY - he is high energy and is looking for an active home that is committed to working on training and helping him become his best adult self. 

Get ready for a wild ride! Marcus is a young bundle of energy who wants to be right beside you through everything! He's a fan of action packed days and nonstop play, but has also been starting to explore the art of chill. This teen puppy is ready to be a lifelong companion for someone (or many someones!) who has energy and some patience to train him through his adolescence to be a VGB forever! This smart boy can learn fast, play hard, then be ready for a good nap at the end!

One Tail at a Time requires that puppies 6 months and under are enrolled in a positive reinforcement training class within 2 weeks of adoption at the adopter's expense.

Marcus' adoption fee is 300. He will be neutered on a future date (2/18/21 at SNIP Society) and a 50 refundable neuter deposit will be required. He is up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will be due for booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Wilbur is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Wilbur is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~1.5 years
Weight: ~42lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! He needs to be kept to a strict schedule
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes some time to settle (10-30 minutes) but overall doing well with his crate training
Dog sociability: Friendly with dogs on walks - may pull/whine/bark in excitement as he wants to greet other dogs. Has done great with other dogs off-leash in playgroup. Enjoys dogs that are his size and playful/active like himself. 
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but we suspect he would do well. May be a little jumpy for very young kiddos, 
Ideal home: A home that can keep him busy both physically and mentally as he is an adolescent guy with some good energy!

Smart, curious, extroverted VGB seeks active, patient human and possibly canine friend for life. Promises to follow you around the house, stare out the window for hours to appease his FOMO (fear of missing out), and give the best cuddles once he gets the zoomies out. Eager to please and very food motivated, Wilbur sits very pretty for the treats and will help immediately with any and all unattended breakfast. Runs a sub 10min mile without even trying and will still play fetch afterward. The cutest piggy snuffles and the biggest tail wags. Seeking mentally stimulating, active lifestyle to satisfy his curious mind, and a yard would be a huge bonus to help with the zoomies! 

Wilbur's adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. He was prescribed Doxycycline recently for a URI and we recommend his adopter follow up with their personal vet if his symptoms worsen.

Missy is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet her.

Missy is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~7 years 
Weight: ~54lbs (should lose some)
Housebroken: Working on it! She needs to be on a strict schedule 
Crate trained: Takes some time (10-30 minutes) and would benefit from continued training for this.
Dog sociability: Missy is reportedly dog-friendly from her transferring shelter partner. In our care, she has been fine meeting dogs on walks but with some dogs she may growl or want to keep walking - may be a little selective, but overall we think she has potential to be fine with the right match.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but can be body sensitive sometimes, so likely best with older kids/teenagers 
Ideal home: Missy is looking for a calm home that can keep her brain busy as she undergoes her heartworm treatment! 

Missy is the sweetest cuddle bug. She's happiest curling up on the couch with you and will do anything for belly scratches. She's a gentle chonky girl with the cutest underbite. She also recently acquired a new skill - STAIRS! She loves people and treats, and sometimes like to sit on the people who give her treats. She's here to live the relaxed life and will spend most of her time sleeping. She's very comfortable being in a home, but will want your attention when she's not sleeping. 

Missy is heartworm positive and will be undergoing treatment at our Ellis Veterinary Clinic. OTAT will cover the cost of her treatment until she is heartworm negative. They will need to remain on exercise restriction for the next ~9 months. For information on the heartworm treatment process, visit: onetail.org/heartworm

Missy's adoption fee is 300. She is spayed, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm positive. She will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense.

animal.description:
Kinnick is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Kinnick is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~7 years 
Weight: ~95lbs (overweight and needs to lose some)
Housebroken: Working on it! He needs to be on a strict schedule. 
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes some time to settle but overall doing well with his crate training
Dog sociability: Friendly. Lives with a dog in his foster home and has done well - he is more of a co-existor. On walks he can be barky and pulls when he sees smaller dogs.
Cat sociability: In his previous home (his home before OTAT) they noted that he was interested and never aggressive towards cats. We have not seen him with cats in our care.
Kids: In his previous home they noted he was friendly with kids. We have not seen him with kids yet in our care. 
Ideal home: Kinnick is a pretty laid back guy looking for a laid back home. He would prefer to not live in an elevator/high-rise situation, but he is adaptable to other living environments. 

Kinnick is the sweetest senior guy! He is a chill dude who loves to play with his stuffed broccoli toy and lounge on the couch. He loves to follow his foster fam around the home and see what they are up to! He is happy to watch some TV with you or help you prepare a yummy dinner - just as long as he gets some snacks along the way! Kinnick lives with a ~70lb playful dog in his foster home and hasn't showed much interest in playing, but he is happy to co-exist with him. This sweet pup is so deserving of the most special forever home!

Kinnick's adoption fee is 150. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will be due for booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. He had an ear infection upon arrival and has been getting medication in foster care. Continued care would be the responsibility of the adopter.

animal.description:
1. PLEASE NOTE: Breed mix info is the best guess of Bark Bark Wag and our vets. There is no way to know for certain what any dog's breed mix is without a DNA test; and most mixed-breed dogs may have 3, 4, 5 different breeds in their mix!  **THERE IS NO WAY TO BE CERTAIN WHETHER THIS DOG IS 'HYPOALLERGENIC', so if you have allergies, this may not be the dog for you.

2. MUST READ --THE FIRST STEP: Go to www.barkbarkwag.org and click on "Let's Get Started!" to learn about our easy 3-step adoption process & apply to adopt! ANSWERS TO MOST QUESTIONS CAN BE FOUND HERE! We are all volunteers with limited time to respond to emails; if your question involves something NOT addressed at "Let's Get Started!", we will respond ASAP!

*WE NEED AN ADOPTION APPLICATION TO START THE PROCESS*

Ella is a lovely, low-to-moderate activity girl. She is 2 1/2 years old, around 75#, and is a mix of Lab & Beagle, best guess.  Ella enjoys cuddling up to watch a movie with you, or will entertain herself if you're working.  She likes to chase a ball or toy, or play a short game of tug of war.  Ella enjoys a walk daily to explore trails; in a quiet, low-traffic area; or sniffing around in a fenced yard. She loves to snuggle in bed with her humans, and burrow under the covers.  Ella is just an all-around easy-to-please girl. She is shy but not needy, and is learning how to ask for attention. She is looking for a calmer adult family who won't rush her into their lives, but will allow her to unfold as she is comfortable and let mutual love/trust grow. 

Ella is a quiet girl who prefers the company of adult humans (the noise and activity of kids is stressful for her) or maybe a cat; she is not comfortable around other dogs. Ella is house-trained and crate-trained; she can be at home alone for 6-8 hours while you work, and she does fine uncrated. She would be happiest with a family who has some larger dog and training experience. Ella can become overstimulated when outside, and is doing well working with a positive reinforcement-based trainer. Bark Bark Wag will provide several sessions with the trainer, to help Ella transition into her forever home. We're looking for a family who can continue with Ella's learning, to help her continue to blossom and be successful in her new home.

animal.description:
Meet Zeek! This sweet boy is almost 2 years old and he REALLY knows how to work the puppy dog eyes! Zeke is a great mix of spunk and chill! He loves going for walks and playing with other dogs but he is also happy to sit with you for snuggles. Zeeks hind end sort of has a mind of its own, when he walks he is a bit wobbly! Zeek has been checked out by a neurologist who found no abnormalities on the MRI, they believe this is something he was born with. Lucky for Zeek he can live a pain free normal life without any extra medical care or maintenance! 

Zeek is currently in foster care with a dog and cat and doing well! The cat has not come out of hiding yet but Zeek did not chase him or try to seek him out once he took off!

Zeek can go up and down stairs with little to no hesitation but for his safety would not do well in a living situation that required him to climb several stair cases. Carpeted stairs are easier (and safer) for him!

Zeek hopes his wobbles dont turn you away! Once you meet him you will fall in love!!

Apply at  http://caninehumane.org/adoption-application/

Adoption Fee is $350
He is up to date on vaccines and has had a wellness exam, heartworm tested and micro-chipped.

 In order to meet any of our dogs, please fill out an application. To fill out an application 
go to http://caninehumane.org/adoption-application/ 

IF THE DOG IS ON PETFINDER THEN IT IS STILL AVAILABLE

www.caninehumane.org

animal.description:
Meet our handsome AND sweet boy named Chuck! This little guy is probably a Pomeranian mix as he has a curled tail and longer, soft hair. Chuck is about 1 year old and only 16 lbs. He looks bigger, but he is mostly hair! He would've been great in an 80's rock band! Rock on little brother!

Chuck is good with other dogs and would probably be fine with cats if he was introduced slowly and appropriately. 

He has a great personality! He is happy, friendly and full of affection. So far, Chuck has been quiet while crated and hasn't pottied inside the foster's home. He likes foster dad too, so no fear with men, YAY!

Chuck is playful and loves to go on walks. He pulls some, but is learning. He is just super excited to be out and about. Chuck would benefit from a basic obedience training class, but that's easy! We love K9 Manners and More in Broken Arrow, they are a great training outfit.

Email us about him today at amyh@rescuednready.com. He will make a great family pet. ADOPTIONS ONLY TO PEOPLE LIVING IN THE NORTHEASTERN OKLAHOMA AREA.  

If you are interested in this dog, please contact volunteer Amy at amyh@rescuednready.com or at 918-688-0755.

The adoption fee is $225.00 and includes all current vaccinations, negative heartworm test, worming, microchip, and spay/neuter surgery.  Go to www.rescuednready.com to learn about our adoption process and download our application.  

CALL or EMAIL US TO MEET ONE OF OUR ADOPTABLE DOGS! Call Amy at 918-688-0755 or email at amyh@rescuednready.com.

animal.description:
AT PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE, WE UPDATE ALL OF OUR PETS ON A REGULAR BASIS TO REFLECT THEIR AVAILABILITY.

IF YOU SEE ME HERE, I AM AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION. PLEASE READ MY BIO BELOW TO LEARN MORE ABOUT ME AND HOW TO APPLY TO ADOPT :)

Meet the F pups:: 8 weeks old on 2/3/21, 8 to 10 pounds, 4 males, 1 female, boxer/beagle/husky mixes.

Accenting Applications, adoptions start on 2/6/21

We were asked to assist with these babies after their mother, a boxer beagle mix, got loose before she was spayed and ended up pregnant by the neighbor's husky. We are paying to spay the mother so this doesn't happen again, and we have inquired about neutering the father, but we're not sure the neighbor will cooperate. 

The mother's owner only wanted what was best for the puppies, so she contacted us to surrender them. While we provided all of their deworming, vaccines and flea/heartworm prevention, she cared for them very well, loved them very much, and they are healthy and well socialized with people, other dogs and children. These puppies have had a wonderful start to life and are now ready to search for their forever homes. They will be medium sized active dogs when grown and will need an active family to keep them busy.

$195 Adoption Fee. 

A $10.00 non-refundable application fee is required to submit your adoption application and will be deducted from your adoption fee if you adopt.

All puppies are dewormed, started on heartworm and flea prevention, and microchipped.

All puppies will be adopted with current, age appropriate vaccines, given by Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue will provide their puppy series DAPP vaccines, given at 8, 12, and 16 weeks of age.

Puppy adopters will be will be required to bring the puppy back to Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue to receive any remaining puppy vaccines after adoption. 

Puppy adopters will also be required to bring the puppy to our vet for their spay/neuter surgery after they receive their 16 week vaccination. 

The spay/neuter and puppy vaccines are included with the puppy adoption fee.

We have a strict one hour puppy adoption radius, puppy adopters must be within one hour of Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. Please see our Adoption Radius tab on our website for more info, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/adoption-radius/

Along with other criteria evaluated in the adoption application, a Fenced Yard is required to adopt. 

Please see our Fenced Yard Requirements tab on our website for more information, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/fenced-yard-requirements/

TO CHECK AVAILABILITY of any of our adoptable animals, please go to our available pets tab, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/available-pets-for-adoption/

All pets listed here are updated regularly to reflect their availability.

ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE:

Before completing the application, please read our ADOPTION PROCESS tab on our website, here: 
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/how-our-adoptions-work/

To complete our easy online adoption application, please visit our website at PeppermintPigAnimalRescue.org.

Adoption events are held every Saturday in our thrift store from 1:00pm to 4:00pm. Please complete your adoption application in advance so our volunteers have time to screen and contact potential adopters.

animal.description:
Sweet Macy is a rambunctious, energetic girl that we rescued from TN as a stray.  She's about 1 1/2 years young Rottweiler mix and weighs a little over 60 lbs. She is incredibly smart, treat motivated, can sit, lay down and patiently waits for her food. She needs an EXPERIENCED firm kind hand.
She loves nothing more than running and playing fetch in the yard. A big fully fenced in yard is a MUST to burn her energy as she is not fond of passing unknown dogs on a walk and is leash reactive. Ideally Macy should be an ONLY dog. NO small children (14+) as she has she gets very excited and jumps on her humans. She would like someone who can be home with her most of the time.
At the end of the day, Macy would love nothing more than to settle down and cuddle with her family.
If you'd like to make this playful energetic girl part of your family, please send an email to jerseygirlsanimalrescue@gmail.com for an application. 

Adoption fee $300

animal.description:
You know the saying, "Find a penny, pick it up. All day long, you'll have good luck" well, we'd like to extend that to our little Chihuahua mix here, except you'll be gaining a lifetime's worth of luck! Penny is about 4 years old and weighing just 14 lbs she'll happily be picked up into your arms. She has gorgeous two-colored eyes and a blonde coat that's even prettier. Penny is still carving out her spot on the farm, but she truly doesn't hope to be here long as the hubbub is all a bit much for her. She'd love to find a quiet adult household where she can live happily snuggled up in the lap of some special person. This Lucky Penny is waiting for you to pick her up, so get in your adoption request right away!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

Wasabi is a 14 month old spayed female Pit Bull Terrier mix. She loves people and is eager to please. She knows "sit" and walks nicely on lead. Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue is a no-kill rescue. Please consider sponsoring a pet or donating to our cause. Click the DONATE tab on our website to learn more about how you can help. THANK YOU!

For questions or inquiries on our adoptable pets, please feel free to contact our volunteer rescue team directly by submitting a Contact Form from our website, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/contact-us/

animal.description:
Freeia - Female
Shepherd/Lab Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 10/1/2020 17 weeks
Current weight 26lbs 

Meet Freeia. She was dumped and abandoned and luckily someone was kind enough to notify the shelter in Arkansas who went and picked her up. She came to Illinois in search of her forever home.  Freeia is the most well behaved puppy, she is sweet, playful and well mannered. She is crate trained, 95% potty trained,(as long as someone is consistent with the needs of a puppy and she goes out often) does very well with children, other dogs, but she has now NOT done well with the families cat. We are at this time saying NO CATS. She is very affectionate, loves attention and being petted and snuggling are her favorites. She is learning basic puppy manners, and is a fast learner. She is so smart. She will make an excellent addition to any family. If interested please fill out an application on our website www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org

WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS 
 
Medical included is as follows:
Spay/Neuter (age appropriate) *Forever Home uses Fox Valley Animal Welfare League in Aurora, IL
Age appropriate core vaccines
Fecal testing and deworming
Flea and tick preventative
Free 1st Vet visit at one of our participating vets
Microchipping
 
Forever Home Dog Rescue reserves the right to deny any applicant.

We know what you're thinking, but just remember none of us pick our own names, and we can assure you, this is the Rhona that you DEFINITELY want! She is a sweet adult lab/terrier mix with an adorable scruffy coat about 3 years old and 50 lbs. She is the friendliest girl who loves giving hugs and taking any opportunity for snuggles from volunteers. She gets along great with other dogs, but having one in her forever home certainly isn't a requirement. Rhona is easy going, but still likes to have a good time! She is a total love who will be so much joy to the home that makes her part of it. Rhona can't wait to meet you and we hope you love her just as much as we do!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Chubb is about 4 months old and his breed in a complete guess. He currently weighs about 15 lbs and we don't think he will get too big but, that is also a guess.

Chubb was found outside as a stray in rural Kentucky. He was underweight and loaded with worms. He is still getting some weight on him but, has been treated for worms and now tested clear.

He is a shy puppy but, opens up quick. In his foster home he lives with 3 big pitbulls and a couple cats. He loves to play with his pittie buddies and to chase the cats! He is working on potty training but, is not perfect. His foster mom says he poops outside only by the treeline because he likes to "hide" when he poops. Privacy? He's also leaning the leash.

We are requiring a fenced yard for Chubb because he spooks easily and feel a fence is safer for him. He would do best in a home with another dog. He likes toys and isn't a big barker so far. 

Chubb is neutered, vaccinated, dewormed, microchipped and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.



Adoption Fee: $300

***We require a complete and approved application before setting up a meet n greet.***

To apply to adopt just copy and paste the link into your search bar!
https://fs24.formsite.com/oneatatimek9rescue/form1/index.html

animal.description:
If you're looking for the happiest and most social pup you've ever met, look no further! Meet Cody! He was adopted 6 years ago and returned to us at no fault of his own. His previous people said he had some skin allergies, so we took him to the vet and he got allergy testing , a cytopoint injection that he needs only on an as needed basis, along with a limited ingredient dog food that he LOVEs! Cody is getting allergy drops daily for immunotherapy with environmental allergies that is already covered and will only need for 9-12 months when his immune system is built up. His skin and fur look AMAZING and he is just like any other pup. His foster mom thinks his past possible skin issues with his previous adopters is a non-issue since she hasn't seen him having any problems now that he is on the limited ingredient food.

Cody is the definition of a wiggle butt and little shadow. He follows his people EVERYWHERE and constantly is wagging his tail. He loves to sleep next to his peeps in the bed but will also be fine in a dog bed on the floor. He is completely house and crate trained. He loves his foster siblings and the puppies in the house as well. They all constantly play, but he loves people way more. Cody is great around kids too! He definitely craves attention and wants to be where you are, so be prepared for all the Cody kisses and snuggles! Cody would do best in a home with someone that is home more often than not and give lots of attention as just because he is 7 he still has quite a bit of energy. A family with kids would be amazing so the kids can keep him busy and play with him! Cody is the easiest and sweetest guy that anyone that adopts him will hit the jackpot!!

Cody is a Male Bichon / Schnauzer Mix that we estimate to be around 7 years old and weighs 23 lbs.

animal.description:
"Can you imagine losing your sight? How about losing everyone and everything you were ever familiar with? How about both at once? How about being blind and moving to new places with new people over and over again? I'm Grace, and that's my story. My newest foster parents say they are determined to help me change that. I am an 8-year-old, medium size, boxer mix with so much love and so many snuggles to give out. I navigate my world through sound, smell, and very cautious feeling. I am the definition of sweetness with all people, just please talk to me so I know who and where you are. I need a special family who will give me TIME and PATIENCE to learn about my new home and our new routine as a family. However, I'll be down for cuddles, kisses, and tail wags day one. Since I can't see them coming, other dogs getting too close to me is very scary. I would do best in a home as the center of your world, but a cat who will keep their distance would be fine. Foster mom and dad are helping me settle here and figuring out what works for me, they can tell you anything they learn and will help in any way they can! I come with an extra support system now. Here's what I've told them so far: I don't like to be kenneled. It's scary, I hit a wall everywhere I turn. I understand potty training and can be very successful with it with a routine. I don't like to be alone, it's frightening in a new place. Music and TV helps me though. My favorite shows are Sofia the First and Curious George, I will tell you if Netflix stops playing! I will continue to learn to grow my independence and confidence while I'm here. Sleep and snuggles are my most favorite pastimes, let's work those in often! I walk GREAT on a leash, which is awesome not only for exercise and potty time, but for helping me learn to navigate my new spaces safely! So, do you think I'm worth it? Could you offer me the forever I've been hoping for? I promise to love you so, so much in return. Please reach out to foster momma with questions. I'm begging, let's make this next move my last move.

All my love and dreams, 
Grace

animal.description:
Please read everything before inquiring. If this dog is still posted, they are still available. Please do not email to ask if this dog is still available. Those emails will not be answered.
Adoption fees for NY dogs is $800 as we are having to use a cargo flying company to bring in the dogs from China. $800 does actually not cover the whole cost. We are fundraising the rest.
We do not know any of the dogs' exact breeds. The listed breeds are just guesses based on how they (or their parents, if known) look.

This is Peanut. He is a stray from China.
2.5 years old. 25 pounds.
 About Peanut:

I was born in a corner of Lilac Lake Garden. This place was originally a rural area. Since the introduction of high-end housing, many people have moved out of this place, but they have left their dogs. It is not uncommon to see a stray dog ??here, but my mother, this extraordinary dog, saved us all. After the five of us were born in the grass, my mother has been rubbing her butt because of a bacterial infection. The volunteer sister was very moved when she saw her returning to the grass with her bleeding butt to breastfeed us and brought our family back to the base. After a while, my mother and little sister were adopted by well-wishers. My third brother went to the United States. The third brother often sent us photos of him riding a yacht and running on a huge lawn. I am very happy to see these. In my dream, I saw that I also have a home.
I am 70cm in length, 50cm in height.
I am very healthy. I am friendly with all dogs and people.
I am a very loyal companion dog. I am well behaved, outgoing and confident.
 


If you are interested in adopting, please fill out the form here:

https://homeboundhoundz.com/application-form

animal.description:
Beautiful Willow is being fostered in NJ. She is in need of a confident owner. Please read Willow's bio below:

Miss Wiggly Willow is a typical puppy for her breed. She doesn't let her sight impairment slow her down at all! She's happy, crazy, wiggly cheerful, and loves to play and have adventures. She's a little nervous around new people, but gets over it quickly with some yummy treats. Very food motivated and super smart. Crates like a dream! Excellently potty trained. Still working on not jumping up on humans, she gets so excited that she forgets. Zero issues with cats. Is very doggy language savvy, a simple quiet growl from another dog and she backs off. She LOVES water! Will happily shower with you every single day. Hasn't jumped up on the counters at all, not even for the cat food. 

She needs a strong human leader though. Someone who will set clear and strict rules. She's smart enough to follow them. Rules make her feel more secure in her life. Willow is still a puppy, she will try getting away with things. Like treat stealing and guarding. A firm, loud, serious correction knocks all thoughts of guarding out of her little brain. She's also familiar with the squirt bottle.  She sometimes forgets not to pull on the leash, but she's getting better at that too. Puppy brains have a hard time concentrating sometimes. Overall she's a very good puppy and wants to be a good girl. She just needs to find the right pet parent(s).
BDRA has voted against the use of electrical fencing effective immediately.

animal.description:
MEET DUKE!  Duke is a 5-year-old Yellow Labrador mix.  He's a smart boy who responds to his name and loves to cuddle!  Duke's is a sweet and friendly doggie requiring a low calorie diet.  He came to VIDA Rescue severely overweight and in need of exercise.  Duke walks well on a leash and is eager to do so.  He's looking for a family or person that will watch his diet and ensure that he gets out of the house daily to burn some calories and have fun doing it!  He's ready for his forever home!

animal.description:
In the words of Muhammad Ali, we're not the greatest; we're the double greatest. Not only do we knock out for our naps but we pick the spot or something like that, right? Rocky and Diamond are an inseparable pair. They love to do everything together and are like two peas in a pod!

Diamond is a mothering type to Rocky, and Rocky is there to keep Diamond calm in unfamiliar places and situations. Diamond is an outgoing, playful dog that loves to cuddle.  She doesn’t like to be left out, so you’ll always find her close by checking out what you’re up to. Diamond loves to play and fetches her toys, but like her brother, also enjoys a nice nap on the couch. She also loves to show off to Rocky by catching her treats mid-air.  Being the mothering type, she’s a bit protective of her brother and humans. She is also a bit hesitant to meet new people, but after a few treats she warms up quickly.

Rocky is a laid-back dog that seems to enjoy carrying his toys around more than playing with them.  Although whenever Diamond asks him to play, he’s up for a game of tug of war or a chase around the yard. Just like his sister, he loves to cuddle. When it's time for a walk, his tail turns into a helicopter, spinning in excitement. During mealtime, he gets a bit protective of his food, so it is best to let him eat separately from Diamond. Based on both Diamond and Rocky’s demeanor, they would be best fit in a home with no small children or other pets.  They love to run and play in the yard, so a larger yard where they can play fetch and tag would be ideal.  They aren't used to being crated and would need to be able to roam freely when left unattended.

The adoption donation for both Rocky & Adrian is $300.

This donation helps to cover veterinary expenses including spay/neuter, microchip and vaccinations. Wish Upon a Rescue is a 501(c)3 non-profit, foster based animal rescue. If you would like to meet Karma and Twinkie, please complete our adoption questionnaire at www.wishuponarescue.org/adopt. We will review your responses and be in contact to schedule a meet and greet at a time and place convenient for your family and our team members.

animal.description:
IN VERMONT

Meet Layla! More pictures and video to come!

Layla is 4 years old (approx. DOB 1-1-17), female, 55 lbs., vetted, is or will be spayed, and micro-chipped. In her current environment Layla is good with other dogs, is crate trained, potty trained, and does exhibit a prey drive toward yard animals so best if she is not with cats. She has medium+ energy, knows Sit, Come, Heel, Wait, Lay Down, Gentle, Off, Leave It, No, and Backup! Layla does alert you when there is people outside and gets very excitable; her best home would be active, experienced, and not have too much stimuli out the windows. Layla is in a home with another dog but might enjoy being the center of attention to build her security!

"Layla wants nothing more than to love you and snuggle you. I have no need for a weighted blanket because I often have her laying on me to snuggle. She is the comedian in the house and has such a big, goofy personality. Her little feet like to dance, she snorts like a pig, and she loves to smoosh her face on yours. When she's sleeping, she sleeps HARD and resembles a ragdoll. She's a giant bed hog and prefers to lay on a people between her people. Layla is a smart one but likes to play stupid until there's something delicious involved. Layla can be difficult and unmannered at times but has a heart of gold and will give unending laughter and love. Layla would do well with another dog that is submissive and similar in size. She would do best with someone who can take her outside to play whether that be in a back yard or out on a trail. As much as she loves people and wants to be by your side, she is fine to be left home while her people are at work. She'd prefer to be left uncrated but will tolerate a crate if needed. Kids would likely be okay as long as they're older, her butt wiggles and long tail can be deadly. She's very much a dog that needs a couch to lay on."

If you are interested in fostering or adopting Layla please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out her Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description:
Ralphie came to us from IACS as a stray. He was listed as urgent because he was very fearful and under-socialized and not adoptable in his current state. We networked hard for this guy and his amazing foster family stepped up for him. He has been settling in and loving life. He’s now ready to find a home of his own! 

Here is what his foster family has to say about him. 

Ralphie has come such a long way! He came to us very timid and fearful. Now, he is full of energy and very affectionate! Ralphie doesn’t know his own size or strength, so it would probably be best if he wasn’t in a home with small children under 5, in case he were to knock them over or climb on them. We have been working on potty training, and he has been doing well! But he will continue to need some ongoing work. Ralphie loooooves other pups! So he should definitely be in a home with other dogs. Just watch out - he loves to play and wrestle! He should also be in a home with a fenced yard, so he can run until his heart’s content and burn off all his energy! We have been crate training him when we leave the house, because he gets very anxious when his ‘people’ leave. If you are looking for a loyal, affectionate, playful dog - Ralphie is your guy!!!!

Ralphie is a family dog and still has some stranger danger. He is still working on proper introductions and learning that new people aren’t scary. Slow intros are best for him! Ralphie is enrolled in a dog class to help with this. If he is moved to trial before classes end, we will have his new family finish them out. 

Ralphie is neutered, microchipped, HW negative and on prevention. Fully vaccinated. He also comes with a GPS tracking collar because he is a flight risk while he adjusts in his new home. It will come with a 1 year paid subscription. His adoption fee is $250. Applications can be found at www.trackingintheshadows.com click on adoptable pets.

animal.description:
Hi world, my name is Trudy! You might remember me as Momma Trudy, who was found living in a drainage pipe with her pups. After two years of eluding capture, I finally found my way into the TLP family, which helped me get my groove back and now I am ready to find my forever home. 

As far as sizes go, I am all about "big things come in small packages. But while I may be petite in stature, my heart is huge and my smile is irresistible. Major cuddle sessions with my human, while being wrapped up in a snuggly blanket, is my jam! I am not a super active dog, and while I enjoy getting some daily exercise, I much prefer the comfort of a couch and some Netflix. Please and thank you! 

Being the chill and low-key gal that I am, I would prefer canine pals that can match my energy. Super active dogs are fun to watch from my window, but I would do best with a lower energy pup who wants to lay around and watch movies with me. I haven't personally met a cat yet, but I don't have much of a prey drive and, with proper introductions, would be happy to peacefully coexist with one. 

I am house trained, crate trained, and I have the best wiggle butt around. So, what are you waiting for? Apply to meet me!

Here's what the rescue from China said about this dog:
I am Sky, I was born in a corner of Dingxiang Lake Garden. This place was originally a rural area. Since the introduction of high-end housing, many people have moved out of this place, but they have left their dogs. It is not uncommon to see a stray dog ??here, but my mother, this extraordinary dog, saved us all. After the five of us were born in the grass, my mother has been rubbing her butt because of a bacterial infection. The volunteer sister was very moved when she saw her returning to the grass with her bleeding butt to breastfeed us and brought our family back to the base. After a while, my mother and little sister were adopted by well-wishers. My third brother went to the United States. The third brother often sent us photos of him riding a yacht and running on a huge lawn. I am very happy to see these. In my dream, I saw that I also have a home. 

Sky's personality: steady, honest, well-behaved and docile.

animal.description:
If you are interested in any of the dogs available at New Leash Rescue, you can reach out to the foster listed below for more information and then complete an adoption application which can be found at https://www.newleashrescue.org/adopt/policy.  Please email the completed application to newleashrescue2018@gmail.com

Thomas is around 2 years old and weighs about 6 pounds.  He is a bit of a shy guy at first and needs some time to warm up- we would recommend him for a quieter home that is used to small dogs.  

Due to his small size and being fragile to squeezing or dropping, we will not place him in a home with kids under age 9.  

He is good with other dogs, and was just neutered and had a dental cleaning.  He will need a housetraining refresher when moving to a new house and a new routine. 

Applications are reviewed in the order received.  

Adoption fee is $450.00 + tax (no checks)

Foster to contact: Katie - kit_n_caboodle22@hotmail.com 

This dog will be at our adoption event at the Woodbury PetSmart on Saturday from 11-2 looking for a home!


Our fosters do the best they can to provide all information about the animal's background and temperament while in foster care in their home. An adopters routine and home environment is likely going to be different than that in their foster home. 

Sometimes there is more that comes out about a dog's personality once they have been able to settle in a home and truly become comfortable. There are great articles out there written about the different stages a pet goes through after adoption, discussing transitions that happen at 3 days, 3 weeks, and 3 months. We highly recommend reading about this - it will help you understand the transition your new pet goes through.
